23// Substitute parameter estimates into the exprs describing the box bounds.
24void substitute_estimates_box(Box &box) {
25 box.used = substitute_var_estimates(box.used);
26 for (auto &b : box.bounds) {
27 b.min = substitute_var_estimates(b.min);
28 b.max = substitute_var_estimates(b.max);
29 }
30}
31
32// Substitute parameter estimates into the boxes in 'region'.
33void substitute_estimates_region(map<string, Box> &region) {
34 for (auto &iter : region) {
35 substitute_estimates_box(iter.second);
36 }
37}
38
39// Return true if any of the box dimension is unbounded.
40bool is_box_unbounded(const Box &b) {
41 for (size_t i = 0; i < b.size(); i++) {
42 if (!b[i].is_bounded()) {
43 return true;
44 }
45 }
46 return false;
47}
48
49// Helper function to simplify the upper and lower bounds of each dimension of a box.
50void simplify_box(Box &b) {
51 for (size_t i = 0; i < b.size(); i++) {
52 b[i].min = simplify(b[i].min);
53 b[i].max = simplify(b[i].max);
54 }
55}
56
57// Helper function to merge the partial region map into the result region map.
58void merge_regions(map<string, Box> &result, const map<string, Box> &partial) {
59 // Merge regions from 'partial' with an existing region in 'result'.
60 for (const auto &reg : partial) {
61 auto iter = result.find(reg.first);
62 if (iter == result.end()) {
63 result.emplace(reg.first, reg.second);
64 } else {
65 merge_boxes(iter->second, reg.second);
66 }
67 }
68}

70// Replace all occurrences of non-alphanumeric chars in 'name' with '_'.
71string get_sanitized_name(string name) {
72 if (isdigit(name[0])) {
73 name = "_" + name;
74 }
75 for (size_t i = 0; i < name.size(); ++i) {
76 if (!isalnum(name[i])) {
77 name[i] = '_';
78 }
79 }
80 return name;
81}

83// Representation of a function stage in the pipeline.
84struct FStage {
85 Function func;
86 uint32_t stage_num;
87 FStage(Function func, uint32_t stage_num)
88 : func(std::move(func)), stage_num(stage_num) {
89 }
90
91 bool operator==(const FStage &other_stage) const {
92 return (func.name() == other_stage.func.name()) &&
93 (stage_num == other_stage.stage_num);
94 }
95
96 bool operator<(const FStage &other_stage) const {
97 return func.name() < other_stage.func.name() ||
98 ((func.name() == other_stage.func.name()) &&
99 (stage_num < other_stage.stage_num));
100 }
101
102 friend std::ostream &operator<<(std::ostream &stream, const FStage &s) {
103 if (s.stage_num == 0) {
104 stream << s.func.name();
105 } else {
106 stream << s.func.name() << ".update(" << (s.stage_num - 1) << ")";
107 }
108 return stream;
109 }
110};

112// Check if all the pipeline outputs have estimates specified
113// on each of their dimensions; otherwise, throw an assertion.
114void check_estimates_on_outputs(const vector<Function> &outputs) {
115 for (const auto &out : outputs) {
116 const vector<Bound> &estimates = out.schedule().estimates();
117 // Check if the estimate for each dimension of the output is available
118 // and is an integer. If there are duplicates for the estimate of a
119 // dimension, we only check the last defined estimate (which min and
120 // extent values are defined) since it is the one that would be
121 // eventually used.
122 Bound est;
123 for (const auto &arg : out.args()) {
124 bool found = false;
125 for (int i = (int)estimates.size() - 1; i >= 0; --i) {
126 if ((estimates[i].var == arg) && estimates[i].min.defined() &&
127 estimates[i].extent.defined()) {
128 found = true;
129 est = estimates[i];
130 break;
131 }
132 }
133 user_assert(found && est.min.type().is_int() && est.extent.type().is_int())
134 << "Please provide a valid estimate for dimension "
135 << arg << " of output \"" << out.name() << "\"\n";
136 }
137 }
138}

140struct DependenceAnalysis {

143 vector<string> order;

146 struct RegionsRequiredQuery {
147 string f;
148 int stage;
149 set<string> prods;
150 bool only_regions_computed;
151
152 RegionsRequiredQuery(const string &f, int stage, const set<string> &prods,
153 bool only_regions_computed)
154 : f(f), stage(stage), prods(prods),
155 only_regions_computed(only_regions_computed) {
156 }
157
158 bool operator==(const RegionsRequiredQuery &other) const {
159 return (f == other.f) && (stage == other.stage) && (prods == other.prods) &&
160 (only_regions_computed == other.only_regions_computed);
161 }
162 bool operator<(const RegionsRequiredQuery &other) const {
163 if (f < other.f) {
164 return true;
165 } else if (f > other.f) {
166 return false;
167 }
168 if (stage < other.stage) {
169 return true;
170 } else if (stage > other.stage) {
171 return false;
172 }
173 if (only_regions_computed < other.only_regions_computed) {
174 return true;
175 } else if (only_regions_computed > other.only_regions_computed) {
176 return false;
177 }
178 return prods < other.prods;
179 }
180 };
181 struct RegionsRequired {
182 DimBounds bounds;
183 // Regions required to compute 'bounds' given a particular
184 // RegionsRequiredQuery.
185 map<string, Box> regions;
186 RegionsRequired(const DimBounds &b, const map<string, Box> &r)
187 : bounds(b), regions(r) {
188 }
189 };
190 // Cache for bounds queries (bound queries with the same parameters are
191 // common during the grouping process).
192 map<RegionsRequiredQuery, vector<RegionsRequired>> regions_required_cache;
193
194 DependenceAnalysis(const map<string, Function> &env, const vector<string> &order,
195 const FuncValueBounds &func_val_bounds)
196 : env(env), order(order), func_val_bounds(func_val_bounds) {
197 }
198
199 // Return the regions of the producers ('prods') required to compute the region
200 // of the function stage ('f', 'stage_num') specified by 'bounds'. When
201 // 'only_regions_computed' is set to true, this only returns the computed
202 // regions and not the total allocated regions.
203 map<string, Box> regions_required(const Function &f, int stage_num,
204 const DimBounds &bounds,
205 const set<string> &prods,
206 bool only_regions_computed,
207 const Scope<Interval> *input_estimates);
208
209 // Return the regions of the producers ('prods') required to compute the region
210 // of the function specified by 'pure_bounds'. When 'only_regions_computed'
211 // is set to true, this only returns the computed regions and not the total
212 // allocated regions.
213 map<string, Box> regions_required(const Function &f,
214 const DimBounds &pure_bounds,
215 const set<string> &prods,
216 bool only_regions_computed,
217 const Scope<Interval> *input_estimates);
218
219 // Return redundantly computed regions of producers ('prods') while computing
220 // a region of the function stage ('f', 'stage_num') specified by 'bounds'.
221 // 'var' is the dimension along which redundant computation is accounted for.
222 // When 'only_regions_computed' is set to true, this only returns the computed
223 // regions and not the total allocated regions. When 'only_regions_computed'
224 // is set to true, this only returns the computed regions and not the total
225 // allocated regions.
226 map<string, Box> redundant_regions(const Function &f, int stage_num, const string &var,
227 const DimBounds &bounds,
228 const set<string> &prods,
229 bool only_regions_computed,
230 const Scope<Interval> *input_estimates);
231
232 // Return overlapping regions of producers ('prods') while computing a function
233 // stage along each of the dimensions.
234 vector<map<string, Box>>
235 overlap_regions(const Function &f, int stage_num, const DimBounds &bounds,
236 const set<string> &prods, bool only_regions_computed,
237 const Scope<Interval> *input_estimates);
238};

240// Return the regions of the producers ('prods') required to compute the region
241// of the function specified by 'pure_bounds'.
242map<string, Box>
243DependenceAnalysis::regions_required(const Function &f, const DimBounds &pure_bounds,
244 const set<string> &prods,
245 bool only_regions_computed,
246 const Scope<Interval> *input_estimates) {
247 // Find the regions required for each stage and merge them.
248 map<string, Box> regions;
249 int num_stages = f.updates().size() + 1;
250 for (int s = 0; s < num_stages; s++) {
251 DimBounds bounds = get_stage_bounds(f, s, pure_bounds);
252 map<string, Box> stage_regions =
253 regions_required(f, s, bounds, prods, only_regions_computed, input_estimates);
254
255 merge_regions(regions, stage_regions);
256 }
257 return regions;
258}

260struct StageBounds {
261 FStage f_stage;
262 DimBounds bounds;
263
264 StageBounds(const FStage &fs, const DimBounds &b)
265 : f_stage(fs), bounds(b) {
266 }
267 StageBounds(Function func, uint32_t stage_num, const DimBounds &b)
268 : f_stage(FStage(std::move(func), stage_num)), bounds(b) {
269 }
270
271 bool operator==(const StageBounds &other) const {
272 return (f_stage == other.f_stage) && (bounds == other.bounds);
273 }
274 bool operator<(const StageBounds &other) const {
275 return (f_stage < other.f_stage) ||
276 ((f_stage == other.f_stage) && (bounds.size() < other.bounds.size()));
277 }
278};

280// Helper function to queue regions that need to be traversed. 'fs_bounds' is
281// the queue into which the regions specified by 'prod_func' and 'region'
282// will be added.
283void queue_func_regions(map<FStage, DimBounds> &fs_bounds,
284 const Function &prod_func, const Box &region,
285 const set<StageBounds> &visited) {
286 DimBounds prod_pure_bounds;
287 const vector<string> &args = prod_func.args();
288
289 internal_assert(region.size() == args.size());
290
291 // The region only specifies the extent of each dimension
292 // by position. Populating a map which is keyed by name.
293 for (size_t v = 0; v < args.size(); v++) {
294 prod_pure_bounds[args[v]] = region[v];
295 }
296
297 // Get the bounds of all stages in a function from the
298 // bounds on the pure dimensions.
299 vector<DimBounds> prod_bounds = get_stage_bounds(prod_func, prod_pure_bounds);
300
301 size_t num_stages = prod_func.updates().size() + 1;
302
303 internal_assert(prod_bounds.size() == num_stages);
304
305 // Add all stages of a function into the queue.
306 for (size_t prod_s = 0; prod_s < num_stages; prod_s++) {
307 StageBounds sb(prod_func, prod_s, prod_bounds[prod_s]);
308 if (visited.find(sb) == visited.end()) {
309 auto iter = fs_bounds.find(sb.f_stage);
310 if (iter == fs_bounds.end()) {
311 fs_bounds.emplace(sb.f_stage, sb.bounds);
312 } else {
313 for (const auto &b : sb.bounds) {
314 DimBounds &curr_bounds = iter->second;
315 auto b_iter = curr_bounds.find(b.first);
316 if (b_iter == curr_bounds.end()) {
317 curr_bounds.emplace(b.first, b.second);
318 } else {
319 if (b_iter->second.has_lower_bound() && b.second.has_lower_bound()) {
320 b_iter->second.min = simplify(Interval::make_min(b_iter->second.min, b.second.min));
321 } else {
322 b_iter->second.min = Interval::neg_inf();
323 }
324
325 if (b_iter->second.has_upper_bound() && b.second.has_upper_bound()) {
326 b_iter->second.max = simplify(Interval::make_max(b_iter->second.max, b.second.max));
327 } else {
328 b_iter->second.max = Interval::pos_inf();
329 }
330 }
331 }
332 }
333 }
334 }
335}

337// Helper function for merging 'curr_regions' to the global map of regions
338// and adding them to the queue of regions that need to be traversed.
339// 'prods' is the set of producer functions that are under consideration.
340void merge_and_queue_regions(map<FStage, DimBounds> &fs_bounds,
341 map<string, Box> &regions,
342 map<string, Box> &curr_regions,
343 const set<string> &prods,
344 const map<string, Function> &env,
345 bool only_regions_computed,
346 const string &curr_func_name,
347 const set<StageBounds> &visited) {
348 for (const auto &reg : curr_regions) {
349 // Merge region with an existing region of a function in the
350 // global map. Do not merge the parent function itself to the region
351 // when querying only for the values computed.
352 if (!only_regions_computed || (only_regions_computed && (reg.first != curr_func_name))) {
353 auto iter = regions.find(reg.first);
354 if (iter == regions.end()) {
355 regions.emplace(reg.first, reg.second);
356 } else {
357 merge_boxes(iter->second, reg.second);
358 }
359 }
360
361 // Skip adding the current region into to the queue if the function
362 // is not in 'prods'.
363 if (prods.find(reg.first) == prods.end()) {
364 continue;
365 }
366
367 const auto &it = env.find(reg.first);
368 if ((it != env.end()) && (reg.first != curr_func_name)) {
369 // Add all stages of the function representing the
370 // region into the queue.
371 queue_func_regions(fs_bounds, it->second, reg.second, visited);
372 }
373 }
374}

376// Return the regions of the producers ('prods') required to compute the region
377// of the function stage ('f', 'stage_num') specified by 'bounds'.
378map<string, Box>
379DependenceAnalysis::regions_required(const Function &f, int stage_num,
380 const DimBounds &bounds,
381 const set<string> &prods,
382 bool only_regions_computed,
383 const Scope<Interval> *input_estimates) {
384 // Iteratively compute the required regions by traversing the chain
385 // of dependencies.
386
387 // Check the cache if we've already computed this previously.
388 RegionsRequiredQuery query(f.name(), stage_num, prods, only_regions_computed);
389 const auto &iter = regions_required_cache.find(query);
390 if (iter != regions_required_cache.end()) {
391 const auto &it = std::find_if(iter->second.begin(), iter->second.end(),
392 [&bounds](const RegionsRequired &r) { return (r.bounds == bounds); });
393 if (it != iter->second.end()) {
394 internal_assert((iter->first == query) && (it->bounds == bounds));
395 return it->regions;
396 }
397 }
398
399 // Map of all the required regions.
400 map<string, Box> regions;
401 map<FStage, DimBounds> fs_bounds;
402 set<StageBounds> visited;
403
404 // Add the query function and its region to the queue.
405 fs_bounds.emplace(FStage(f, stage_num), bounds);
406
407 while (!fs_bounds.empty()) {
408 for (int i = order.size() - 1; i >= 0; --i) {
409 const Function &f = env.find(order[i])->second;
410 int num_stages = f.updates().size() + 1;
411 for (int stage_num = 0; stage_num < num_stages; ++stage_num) {
412 FStage s(f, stage_num);
413
414 const auto &iter = fs_bounds.find(s);
415 if (iter == fs_bounds.end()) {
416 continue;
417 }
418
419 DimBounds curr_bounds = iter->second;
420 visited.insert(StageBounds(s, curr_bounds));
421
422 // Scope for containing all the estimates on parameters and intervals.
423 Scope<Interval> curr_scope;
424 curr_scope.set_containing_scope(input_estimates);
425
426 // If the function has an extern definition, there is no visibility into
427 // the expression defining the function. So the regions required will be
428 // the entire domain of the inputs to the extern func. Use the estimates
429 // on the inputs to the extern function if available.
430 //
431 // TODO: Query the extern function for bounds of the functions which it
432 // it depends on. This can be done by calling the extern func in the
433 // bounds query mode.
434 if (s.func.has_extern_definition()) {
435 for (const ExternFuncArgument &arg : s.func.extern_arguments()) {
436 if (arg.is_func()) {
437 // If the argument is an entire function, the bounds of the
438 // function required are unknown. Create an infinite region
439 // of the correct dimension, update the region map, and
440 // add it to the queue.
441 string prod_name = Function(arg.func).name();
442 const Function &prod_func = get_element(env, prod_name);
443 map<string, Box> prod_reg;
444 const vector<string> &args = prod_func.args();
445 for (size_t v = 0; v < args.size(); v++) {
446 prod_reg[prod_name].push_back(Interval());
447 }
448 merge_and_queue_regions(fs_bounds, regions, prod_reg, prods, env,
449 only_regions_computed, s.func.name(), visited);
450 } else if (arg.is_expr()) {
451 // Find the boxes required for the expression and add the regions
452 // to the queue.
453 Expr subs_arg = substitute_var_estimates(arg.expr);
454 map<string, Box> arg_regions = boxes_required(subs_arg, curr_scope, func_val_bounds);
455 substitute_estimates_region(arg_regions);
456 merge_and_queue_regions(fs_bounds, regions, arg_regions, prods, env,
457 only_regions_computed, s.func.name(), visited);
458 } else if (arg.is_image_param() || arg.is_buffer()) {
459 // If the argument is an image or a buffer, the required
460 // bounds are unknown. Create an infinite region of the
461 // correct dimension and update the region map.
462 Buffer<> buf;
463 if (arg.is_image_param()) {
464 buf = arg.image_param.buffer();
465 } else {
466 buf = arg.buffer;
467 }
468 map<string, Box> buf_reg;
469 for (int v = 0; v < buf.dimensions(); v++) {
470 buf_reg[buf.name()].push_back(Interval());
471 }
472 merge_regions(regions, buf_reg);
473 }
474 }
475 } else {
476 Definition def = get_stage_definition(s.func, s.stage_num);
477 const vector<Dim> &dims = def.schedule().dims();
478
479 // Substitute parameter estimates into the bounds and add them to the
480 // current scope.
481 for (int d = 0; d < (int)dims.size() - 1; d++) {
482 Interval simple_bounds = get_element(curr_bounds, dims[d].var);
483 simple_bounds.min = substitute_var_estimates(simple_bounds.min);
484 simple_bounds.max = substitute_var_estimates(simple_bounds.max);
485 curr_scope.push(dims[d].var, simple_bounds);
486 }
487
488 // Find the regions required for each value of the current function stage,
489 // update the region map, and add them to the queue.
490 for (const auto &val : def.values()) {
491 // Substitute the parameter estimates into the expression and get
492 // the regions required for the expression.
493 Expr subs_val = substitute_var_estimates(val);
494 map<string, Box> curr_regions = boxes_required(subs_val, curr_scope, func_val_bounds);
495 substitute_estimates_region(curr_regions);
496
497 // Arguments to the definition may require regions of functions.
498 // For example, update definitions in histograms where the bin is
499 // based on the value of a function.
500 Box left_reg;
501 for (const Expr &arg : def.args()) {
502 Expr subs_arg = substitute_var_estimates(arg);
503 map<string, Box> arg_regions = boxes_required(subs_arg, curr_scope, func_val_bounds);
504 substitute_estimates_region(arg_regions);
505
506 // Merge the regions with the regions found while looking at
507 // the values.
508 merge_regions(curr_regions, arg_regions);
509
510 Interval arg_bounds = bounds_of_expr_in_scope(arg, curr_scope, func_val_bounds);
511 left_reg.push_back(arg_bounds);
512 }
513
514 auto iter_curr = curr_regions.find(s.func.name());
515 if (iter_curr == curr_regions.end()) {
516 curr_regions.emplace(s.func.name(), left_reg);
517 } else {
518 merge_boxes(iter_curr->second, left_reg);
519 }
520
521 // Update the region map, and add 'curr_regions' to the queue.
522 merge_and_queue_regions(fs_bounds, regions, curr_regions, prods, env,
523 only_regions_computed, s.func.name(), visited);
524 }
525 }
526
527 // Remove processed region from the queue.
528 fs_bounds.erase(iter);
529 }
530 }
531 }
532
533 // Simplify the bounds on each region and substitute global pipeline
534 // bounds for function regions which lower and upper bounds could not be
535 // determined.
536 map<string, Box> concrete_regions;
537
538 for (auto &f_reg : regions) {
539 simplify_box(f_reg.second);
540
541 Box concrete_box;
542 for (size_t i = 0; i < f_reg.second.size(); i++) {
543 Expr lower = f_reg.second[i].min;
544 Expr upper = f_reg.second[i].max;
545
546 auto iter = env.find(f_reg.first);
547 bool in_env = (iter != env.end());
548
549 if (!lower.as<IntImm>() && in_env) {
550 const Function &curr_f = iter->second;
551 for (const auto &b : curr_f.schedule().estimates()) {
552 size_t num_pure_args = curr_f.args().size();
553 if ((i < num_pure_args) && (b.var == curr_f.args()[i])) {
554 lower = b.min;
555 }
556 }
557 }
558
559 if (!upper.as<IntImm>() && in_env) {
560 const Function &curr_f = iter->second;
561 for (const auto &b : curr_f.schedule().estimates()) {
562 size_t num_pure_args = curr_f.args().size();
563 if ((i < num_pure_args) && (b.var == curr_f.args()[i])) {
564 const IntImm *bmin = b.min.as<IntImm>();
565 const IntImm *bextent = b.extent.as<IntImm>();
566 upper = IntImm::make(Int(32), bmin->value + bextent->value - 1);
567 }
568 }
569 }
570
571 Interval concrete_bounds = Interval(lower, upper);
572 concrete_box.push_back(concrete_bounds);
573 }
574 concrete_regions[f_reg.first] = concrete_box;
575 }
576
577 regions_required_cache[query].push_back(RegionsRequired(bounds, concrete_regions));
578 return concrete_regions;
579}

581// Return redundantly computed regions of producers ('prods') while computing a
582// region of the function stage ('f', 'stage_num') specified by 'bounds'. 'var'
583// is the dimension along which redundant computation is accounted for.
584map<string, Box>
585DependenceAnalysis::redundant_regions(const Function &f, int stage_num, const string &var,
586 const DimBounds &bounds,
587 const set<string> &prods,
588 bool only_regions_computed,
589 const Scope<Interval> *input_estimates) {
590 // Find the regions required to compute the region of 'f' specified
591 // by 'bounds'.
592 map<string, Box> regions = regions_required(
593 f, stage_num, bounds, prods, only_regions_computed, input_estimates);
594
595 // Shift the bounds by the size of the interval along the direction
596 // of var.
597 DimBounds shifted_bounds;
598
599 for (const auto &b : bounds) {
600 if (b.first == var) {
601 Expr len = b.second.max - b.second.min + 1;
602 Interval bound = Interval(b.second.min + len, b.second.max + len);
603 shifted_bounds[b.first] = bound;
604 } else {
605 shifted_bounds[b.first] = b.second;
606 }
607 }
608
609 // Find the regions required to compute the region of f specified
610 // by shifted_bounds.
611 map<string, Box> regions_shifted = regions_required(
612 f, stage_num, shifted_bounds, prods, only_regions_computed, input_estimates);
613
614 // Compute the overlaps between 'regions_shifted' and the original
615 // regions required.
616 map<string, Box> overlaps;
617 for (const auto &reg : regions) {
618 auto iter = regions_shifted.find(reg.first);
619 if (iter == regions.end()) {
620 // It will be interesting to log cases where this actually happens
621 // i.e., the shifted regions do not contain a function that was
622 // there in the original regions.
623 continue;
624 }
625 const Box &b = reg.second;
626 const Box &b_shifted = iter->second;
627 // The boxes should be of the same size.
628 internal_assert(b.size() == b_shifted.size());
629
630 Box b_intersect;
631 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < b.size(); i++) {
632 b_intersect.push_back(Interval::make_intersection(b[i], b_shifted[i]));
633 }
634 // A function should appear once in the regions and therefore cannot
635 // already be present in the overlaps map.
636 internal_assert(overlaps.find(reg.first) == overlaps.end());
637 overlaps.emplace(reg.first, b_intersect);
638 }
639
640 // Simplify the bounds of each of the overlap regions.
641 for (auto &f : overlaps) {
642 simplify_box(f.second);
643 }
644
645 return overlaps;
646}

648// Return overlapping regions of producers ('prods') while computing a function
649// stage along each of the dimensions.
650vector<map<string, Box>>
651DependenceAnalysis::overlap_regions(const Function &f, int stage_num,
652 const DimBounds &bounds,
653 const set<string> &prods,
654 bool only_regions_computed,
655 const Scope<Interval> *input_estimates) {
656 vector<map<string, Box>> conc_overlaps;
657
658 const vector<Dim> &dims = get_stage_dims(f, stage_num);
659
660 // Get the redundant regions along each dimension of f.
661 for (int d = 0; d < (int)dims.size() - 1; d++) {
662 map<string, Box> conc_reg = redundant_regions(f, stage_num, dims[d].var, bounds,
663 prods, only_regions_computed, input_estimates);
664 conc_overlaps.push_back(conc_reg);
665 }
666 return conc_overlaps;
667}
668
669// Return the regions of each function required for computing the
670// outputs of the pipeline.
671map<string, Box> get_pipeline_bounds(DependenceAnalysis &analysis,
672 const vector<Function> &outputs,
673 const Scope<Interval> *input_estimates) {
674 map<string, Box> pipeline_bounds;
675
676 // Find the regions required for each of the outputs and merge them
677 // to compute the full pipeline_bounds.
678 for (const auto &out : outputs) {
679 DimBounds pure_bounds;
680 Box out_box;
681 // Use the estimates on the output for determining the output bounds.
682 // If there are duplicates, use the most recent estimate.
683 const auto &estimates = out.schedule().estimates();
684 for (const auto &arg : out.args()) {
685 int i;
686 for (i = estimates.size() - 1; i >= 0; --i) {
687 const auto &est = estimates[i];
688 if ((est.var == arg) && est.min.defined() && est.extent.defined()) {
689 Interval in = Interval(est.min, simplify(est.min + est.extent - 1));
690 pure_bounds.emplace(arg, in);
691 out_box.push_back(in);
692 break;
693 }
694 }
695 internal_assert(i >= 0) << "Could not find estimate for " << arg << "\n";
696 }
697
698 set<string> prods;
699 for (const pair<const string, Function> &fpair : analysis.env) {
700 prods.insert(fpair.first);
701 }
702
703 map<string, Box> regions = analysis.regions_required(out, pure_bounds, prods,
704 false, input_estimates);
705
706 // Add the output region to the pipeline bounds as well.
707 regions.emplace(out.name(), out_box);
708
709 merge_regions(pipeline_bounds, regions);
710 }
711
712 return pipeline_bounds;
713}
714
715struct AutoSchedule {
716 struct Stage {
717 string function;
718 size_t stage;
719
720 Stage(const string &f, size_t s)
721 : function(f), stage(s) {
722 }
723
724 bool operator==(const Stage &other) const {
725 return (function == other.function) && (stage == other.stage);
726 }
727 bool operator<(const Stage &other) const {
728 return (function < other.function) || ((function == other.function) && (stage < other.stage));
729 }
730 };
731
732 const map<string, Function> &env;
733
734 // Contain maps from function name to the topological order of the pipeline.
735 map<string, size_t> topological_order;
736
737 // Cache for storing all internal vars/rvars that have been declared during
738 // the course of schedule generation, to ensure that we don't introduce any
739 // duplicates in the string representation of the schedules.
740 map<string, VarOrRVar> internal_vars;
741
742 // Store the list of schedules applied to some function stages (most recent
743 // schedule is placed last in the list).
744 map<string, map<int, vector<string>>> func_schedules;
745
746 // Store the list of vars/rvars used in the schedule applied to some
747 // function stages.
748 map<string, map<int, set<string>>> used_vars;
749
750 AutoSchedule(const map<string, Function> &env, const vector<string> &order)
751 : env(env) {
752 for (size_t i = 0; i < order.size(); ++i) {
753 topological_order.emplace(order[i], i);
754 }
755 // Allocate a slot in 'used_vars' for each function stages in the pipeline
756 for (const auto &iter : env) {
757 for (size_t i = 0; i < iter.second.updates().size() + 1; ++i) {
758 used_vars[iter.first][i];
759 }
760 }
761 }
762
763 // Given a function name, return a string representation of getting the
764 // function handle
765 string get_func_handle(const string &name) const {
766 size_t index = get_element(topological_order, name);
767 return "pipeline.get_func(" + std::to_string(index) + ")";
768 }
769
770 friend std::ostream &operator<<(std::ostream &stream, const AutoSchedule &sched) {
771 for (const auto &iter : sched.internal_vars) {
772 if (iter.second.is_rvar) {
773 stream << "RVar ";
774 } else {
775 stream << "Var ";
776 }
777 stream << iter.first << "(\"" << iter.first << "\");\n";
778 }
779 stream << "\n";
780
781 // Declare all the functions + schedules
782 std::ostringstream func_ss;
783 std::ostringstream schedule_ss;
784
785 for (const auto &f : sched.func_schedules) {
786 const string &fname = get_sanitized_name(f.first);
787 func_ss << "Func " << fname << " = " << sched.get_func_handle(f.first) << ";\n";
788
789 schedule_ss << "{\n";
790
791 // Declare all the Vars and RVars that are actually used in the schedule
792 const Function &func = get_element(sched.env, f.first);
793 for (size_t i = 0; i < func.args().size(); ++i) {
794 if (sched.used_vars.at(func.name()).at(0).find(func.args()[i]) != sched.used_vars.at(func.name()).at(0).end()) {
795 schedule_ss << " Var " << func.args()[i] << " = "
796 << fname << ".args()[" << i << "];\n";
797 }
798 }
799 set<string> declared_rvars;
800 for (size_t i = 0; i < func.updates().size(); ++i) {
801 const vector<ReductionVariable> &rvars = func.updates()[i].schedule().rvars();
802 const set<string> &var_list = sched.used_vars.at(func.name()).at(i + 1);
803 for (size_t j = 0; j < rvars.size(); ++j) {
804 if ((var_list.find(rvars[j].var) == var_list.end()) ||
805 (declared_rvars.find(rvars[j].var) != declared_rvars.end())) {
806 continue;
807 }
808 declared_rvars.insert(rvars[j].var);
809 schedule_ss << " RVar " << rvars[j].var << "("
810 << fname << ".update(" << i << ").get_schedule().rvars()[" << j << "].var);\n";
811 }
812 }
813
814 for (const auto &s : f.second) {
815 internal_assert(!s.second.empty());
816 schedule_ss << " " << fname;
817 if (s.first > 0) {
818 schedule_ss << ".update(" << std::to_string(s.first - 1) << ")";
819 }
820 for (size_t i = 0; i < s.second.size(); ++i) {
821 schedule_ss << "\n ." << s.second[i];
822 }
823 schedule_ss << ";\n";
824 }
825
826 schedule_ss << "}\n";
827 }
828
829 stream << func_ss.str() << "\n";
830 stream << schedule_ss.str() << "\n";
831
832 return stream;
833 }
834
835 void push_schedule(const string &stage_name, size_t stage_num,
836 const string &sched, const set<string> &vars) {
837 vector<string> v = split_string(stage_name, ".");
838 internal_assert(!v.empty());
839
840 used_vars[v[0]][stage_num].insert(vars.begin(), vars.end());
841
842 // If the previous schedule applied is the same as this one,
843 // there is no need to re-apply the schedule
844 auto &schedules = func_schedules[v[0]][stage_num];
845 if (schedules.empty()) {
846 schedules.push_back(sched);
847 } else {
848 if (schedules[schedules.size() - 1] != sched) {
849 schedules.push_back(sched);
850 }
851 }
852 }
853};

855// Implement the grouping algorithm and the cost model for making the grouping
856// choices.
857struct Partitioner {
858 // GroupingChoice encodes the grouping of the 'prod' function into the 'cons' stage.
859 struct GroupingChoice {
860 string prod;
861 FStage cons;
862
863 GroupingChoice(const string &prod, const FStage &cons)
864 : prod(prod), cons(cons) {
865 }
866
867 bool operator==(const GroupingChoice &other) const {
868 return (prod == other.prod) && (cons == other.cons);
869 }
870
871 bool operator<(const GroupingChoice &other) const {
872 return (prod < other.prod) || ((prod == other.prod) && (cons < other.cons));
873 }
874
875 friend std::ostream &operator<<(std::ostream &stream, const GroupingChoice &choice) {
876 stream << "Choice: " << choice.prod << " -> " << choice.cons << "\n";
877 return stream;
878 }
879 };
880
881 // A group is a sub-pipeline with a single output. Members of a group are
882 // either inlined into the consumer functions within the group or computed
883 // at tiles of the output, specified by 'tile_sizes'.
884 //
885 // TODO: The restriction of computing either at the inline or tile level
886 // makes the space of scheduling choices for a group very tractable.
887 // However, the restriction might miss good schedules which can only be
888 // realized by computing the members of the group at different levels of
889 // the group.
890 //
891 // There are two approaches to extend the space of schedules considered:
892 // 1) Recursive grouping: Treat the problem of determining the compute levels
893 // within a group as a smaller instance of the grouping problem with
894 // different parameters for the input, output sizes, and cache model.
895 //
896 // 2) Tightening: Always compute a function at the lowest level possible
897 // without introducing redundant work. This is a restricted form of recursive
898 // grouping which does not explore the trade-off between redundant work and
899 // locality.
900 //
901 // Either approach can be implemented as a post process for each group
902 // after the initial grouping process finishes. The cost model may
903 // already make sub-optimal higher level partitioning when it is not aware
904 // of the benefits of the post processing. However, it should strictly be
905 // an improvement over the initial grouping. As a first step, it is good
906 // to make it a post process.
907 //
908 // Incorporating the recursive grouping process into the cost model can be
909 // tricky and can potentially make the cost of analyzing a group
910 // prohibitive, as it requires solving smaller instances of the grouping
911 // problem for analyzing each configuration. On the other hand, tightening
912 // can be integrated into the cost model with out significantly increasing
913 // the time to analyze a grouping configuration.
914 //
915 // TODO: Add sliding window optimizations. For start, it may be enough to
916 // implement sliding window as a post-pass by moving the store level of all
917 // the members of the group to the outermost serial loop. This could possibly
918 // be incorporated in the cost model with some effort. Line-buffering
919 // presents additional challenges for this post-processing strategy though.
920 // A typical line-buffer would use terrible tile size for tiling, but its
921 // performance will improve significantly once sliding window is turned on.
922 //
923 // TODO: Register tiling is an important transformation especially for
924 // benchmarks with significant reuse of the data (like matrix multiply and
925 // convolutional layers). The mechanism for realizing register tiling is to
926 // completely unroll small tiles of the innermost kernels. Unrolling
927 // interacts with vectorization, storage layout, and depends on the outer
928 // level tiling.
929 struct Group {
930 // The output stage representing the group.
931 FStage output;
932 // Functions that belong to the group.
933 vector<FStage> members;
934 // Members of the group which are inlined.
935 set<string> inlined;
936 // Tile sizes along dimensions of the output function of the group.
937 map<string, Expr> tile_sizes;
938
939 Group(const FStage &output, const vector<FStage> &members)
940 : output(output), members(members) {
941 }
942
943 friend std::ostream &operator<<(std::ostream &stream, const Group &g) {
944 stream << "Output FStage: " << g.output << "\n"
945 << "Members: {";
946 for (size_t i = 0; i < g.members.size(); ++i) {
947 if (i > 0) {
948 stream << ", ";
949 }
950 stream << g.members[i];
951 }
952 stream << "}\n";
953
954 stream << "Inlined: {";
955 for (auto iter = g.inlined.begin(); iter != g.inlined.end(); ++iter) {
956 if (std::distance(g.inlined.begin(), iter) > 0) {
957 stream << ", ";
958 }
959 stream << *iter;
960 }
961 stream << "}\n";
962
963 stream << "Tile sizes: {";
964 for (auto iter = g.tile_sizes.begin(); iter != g.tile_sizes.end(); ++iter) {
965 if (std::distance(g.tile_sizes.begin(), iter) > 0) {
966 stream << ", ";
967 }
968 stream << "(" << iter->first << ", " << iter->second << ")";
969 }
970 stream << "}\n";
971
972 return stream;
973 }
974 };
975
976 // Result of the analysis of a group.
977 struct GroupAnalysis {
978 // Estimate of the arithmetic and memory cost for computing the group.
979 Cost cost;
980 // Estimate of the parallelism that can be exploited while computing
981 // the group.
982 Expr parallelism;
983
984 GroupAnalysis()
985 : cost(Cost()), parallelism(Expr()) {
986 }
987 GroupAnalysis(const Cost &c, Expr p)
988 : cost(c), parallelism(std::move(p)) {
989 }
990
991 inline bool defined() const {
992 return cost.defined() && parallelism.defined();
993 }
994
995 void simplify() {
996 cost.simplify();
997 if (parallelism.defined()) {
998 parallelism = Internal::simplify(parallelism);
999 }
1000 }
1001
1002 friend std::ostream &operator<<(std::ostream &stream, const GroupAnalysis &analysis) {
1003 stream << "[arith cost:" << analysis.cost.arith << ", "
1004 << "memory cost:" << analysis.cost.memory << ", "
1005 << "parallelism:" << analysis.parallelism << "]\n";
1006 return stream;
1007 }
1008 };

1010 // Configuration of a group and the corresponding analysis. A group is the
1011 // set of functions that are computed together in tiles and the group config
1012 // specifies at what granularity they are computed together ('tile_sizes').
1013 struct GroupConfig {
1014 map<string, Expr> tile_sizes;
1015 GroupAnalysis analysis;
1016 GroupConfig(const map<string, Expr> &tile_sizes, const GroupAnalysis &analysis)
1017 : tile_sizes(tile_sizes), analysis(analysis) {
1018 }
1019 GroupConfig()
1020 : tile_sizes(map<string, Expr>()), analysis(GroupAnalysis()) {
1021 }

1024 // Cache for storing the best configuration for the grouping choice. During
1025 // the grouping process, the impact of grouping two groups together is only
1026 // limited to the producers and consumers of the groups that are being grouped
1027 // together. The best grouping choices for the rest of the pipeline need not be
1028 // re-evaluated and caching them improves performance significantly.
1029 map<GroupingChoice, GroupConfig> grouping_cache;
1030
1031 // Each group in the pipeline has a single output stage. A group is comprised
1032 // of function stages that are computed together in tiles (stages of a function
1033 // are always grouped together). 'groups' is the mapping from the output stage
1034 // of the group to the group.
1035 map<FStage, Group> groups;
1036 // The child stages of each stage (i.e. stages that depend on or use the values
1037 // computed by a particular stage) in the pipeline.
1038 map<FStage, set<FStage>> children;
1039 // Map from the output stage of the group to the analysis of the group. The mapping
1040 // needs to be updated whenever the grouping changes.
1041 map<FStage, GroupAnalysis> group_costs;
1042
1043 // Levels that are targeted by the grouping algorithm. In the 'Inline' mode, the grouping
1044 // algorithm groups the functions by inlining the expression for the producer function
1045 // into the consumer stage. In the 'FastMem' mode, the grouping is done at the level of
1046 // tiles of the group output stage.
1047 enum class Level { Inline,
1048 FastMem };
1049
1050 // Bounds of each function stage in the pipeline. These bounds are inferred from the
1051 // estimates of the outputs and other functions in the pipeline.
1052 const map<string, Box> &pipeline_bounds;

1054 // group in the pipeline.

1056 // Dependency analysis of the pipeline. This support queries on regions
1057 // accessed and computed for producing some regions of some functions.
1058 DependenceAnalysis &dep_analysis;
1059 // The arithmetic and memory costs of evaluating the expressions which define
1060 // each function in the pipeline.
1061 RegionCosts &costs;
1062 // Output functions of the pipeline.
1063 const vector<Function> &outputs;
1064
1065 Partitioner(const map<string, Box> &_pipeline_bounds,
1066 const MachineParams &_arch_params,
1067 const vector<Function> &_outputs,
1068 DependenceAnalysis &_dep_analysis,
1069 RegionCosts &_costs);

1074 // will be the output stage of the merged group.

1077 // Merge 'prods' in 'choice' into 'cons'. Set the tile size of the new group

1087 // For each group in the partition, return the regions of the producers

1095 // Partition the pipeline by iteratively merging groups until a fixpoint is

1100 // the highest estimated benefits.

1129 // Estimate the benefit (arithmetic + memory) of 'new_grouping' over 'old_grouping'.
1130 // Positive values indicates that 'new_grouping' may be preferrable over 'old_grouping'.

1166 // following their grouping structure.
1167 //
1168 // TODO: A mode where schedules are not applied to the functions might be
1169 // interesting.
1170 //
1171 // TODO: The current form of the schedule returned is not very useful since it
1172 // cannot be manipulated and introspected very easily. The problem is that all

1252Cost Partitioner::get_pipeline_cost() {
1253 internal_assert(!group_costs.empty());
1254
1255 Cost total_cost(0, 0);
1256 for (const pair<const FStage, Group> &g : groups) {
1257 const GroupAnalysis &analysis = get_element(group_costs, g.first);
1258 if (!analysis.cost.defined()) {
1259 return Cost();
1260 }
1261 total_cost.arith += analysis.cost.arith;
1262 total_cost.memory += analysis.cost.memory;
1263 }
1264 total_cost.simplify();
1265 return total_cost;
1266}
1267
1268void Partitioner::disp_pipeline_costs() {
1269 internal_assert(!group_costs.empty());
1270 Cost total_cost(0, 0);
1271 debug(0) << "\n===============\n"
1272 << "Pipeline costs:\n"
1273 << "===============\n"
1274 << "Group: (name) [arith cost, mem cost, parallelism]\n";
1275 for (const pair<const FStage, Group> &g : groups) {
1276 const GroupAnalysis &analysis = get_element(group_costs, g.first);
1277 if (!total_cost.arith.defined()) {
1278 continue;
1279 } else if (!analysis.cost.arith.defined()) {
1280 total_cost.arith = Expr();
1281 } else {
1282 total_cost.arith += analysis.cost.arith;
1283 }
1284
1285 if (!total_cost.memory.defined()) {
1286 continue;
1287 } else if (!analysis.cost.memory.defined()) {
1288 total_cost.memory = Expr();
1289 } else {
1290 total_cost.memory += analysis.cost.memory;
1291 }
1292
1293 debug(0) << "Group: " << g.first << " [";
1294 debug(0) << analysis.cost.arith << ", " << analysis.cost.memory
1295 << ", " << analysis.parallelism << "]\n";
1296 }
1297 total_cost.simplify();
1298 debug(0) << "Total arithmetic cost: " << total_cost.arith << "\n"
1299 << "Total memory cost: " << total_cost.memory << "\n"
1300 << "===============\n";
1301}
1302
1303// Construct a partitioner and build the pipeline graph on which the grouping
1304// algorithm operates.
1305Partitioner::Partitioner(const map<string, Box> &_pipeline_bounds,
1306 const MachineParams &_arch_params,
1307 const vector<Function> &_outputs,
1308 DependenceAnalysis &_dep_analysis,
1309 RegionCosts &_costs)
1310 : pipeline_bounds(_pipeline_bounds), arch_params(_arch_params),
1311 dep_analysis(_dep_analysis), costs(_costs), outputs(_outputs) {
1312 // Place each stage of a function in its own group. Each stage is
1313 // a node in the pipeline graph.
1314 for (const auto &f : dep_analysis.env) {
1315 if (!pipeline_bounds.count(f.first)) {
1316 // If a function does not have a pipeline bound (i.e. it can be
1317 // statically proven that no one ever uses it), we should not
1318 // consider it during the grouping.
1319 debug(5) << "Creating partitioner: ignore function \"" << f.first
1320 << "\" since it has empty pipeline bounds\n";
1321 continue;
1322 }
1323 int num_stages = f.second.updates().size() + 1;
1324 for (int s = 0; s < num_stages; s++) {
1325 FStage stg(f.second, s);
1326 Group g(stg, {stg});
1327 groups.insert(make_pair(stg, g));
1328 }
1329 }
1330
1331 // Find the consumers of each function and use it to populate the children map.
1332 for (const auto &f : dep_analysis.env) {
1333 int num_stages = f.second.updates().size() + 1;
1334 for (int s = 0; s < num_stages; s++) {
1335 set<string> parents = get_parents(f.second, s);
1336 for (const string &c : parents) {
1337 // Filter out the calls to pipeline inputs. 'env' only contains
1338 // the functions computed and not the inputs.
1339 auto iter = dep_analysis.env.find(c);
1340 if ((c != f.first) && (iter != dep_analysis.env.end())) {
1341 // Consumer depends only on the last stage of a producer
1342 // with multiple stages.
1343 const Function &prod_func = iter->second;
1344 int final_stage = prod_func.updates().size();
1345
1346 FStage prod_stage(prod_func, final_stage);
1347 FStage cons_stage(f.second, s);
1348 children[prod_stage].insert(cons_stage);
1349 }
1350 }
1351
1352 if (s > 0) {
1353 // Update the children map to reflect the dependencies between
1354 // different stages of the same function.
1355 FStage prod_stage(f.second, s - 1);
1356 FStage cons_stage(f.second, s);
1357 children[prod_stage].insert(cons_stage);
1358 }
1359 }
1360 }
1361}
1362
1363void Partitioner::initialize_groups() {
1364 for (pair<const FStage, Group> &g : groups) {
1365 pair<map<string, Expr>, GroupAnalysis> best = find_best_tile_config(g.second);
1366 g.second.tile_sizes = best.first;
1367 group_costs.emplace(g.second.output, best.second);
1368 }
1369 grouping_cache.clear();
1370}
1371
1372map<string, Expr> Partitioner::evaluate_reuse(const FStage &stg,
1373 const set<string> &prods) {
1374 map<string, Expr> reuse;
1375 Function f = stg.func;
1376
1377 // TODO: Check if tile size of 1 in each dimension gives a reasonable
1378 // answer or reuse should be evaluated at a much larger granularity or
1379 // symbolically. Using a symbolic version might be better if the objective
1380 // is to prove the dimension has no reuse. The only downside with the
1381 // symbolic method is that it is totally at the mercy of the simplifier.
1382 // Another option is sampling or using a larger granularity.
1383 map<string, Expr> tile_sizes;
1384
1385 const vector<Dim> &dims = get_stage_dims(stg.func, stg.stage_num);
1386 for (int d = 0; d < (int)dims.size() - 1; d++) {
1387 tile_sizes[dims[d].var] = 1;
1388 }
1389
1390 DimBounds bounds = get_bounds_from_tile_sizes(stg, tile_sizes);
1391
1392 vector<map<string, Box>> reuse_regions =
1393 dep_analysis.overlap_regions(stg.func, stg.stage_num, bounds, prods,
1394 false, &costs.input_estimates);
1395
1396 for (int d = 0; d < (int)dims.size() - 1; d++) {
1397 Expr total_reuse = make_zero(Int(64));
1398 if (debug::debug_level() >= 3) {
1399 disp_regions(reuse_regions[d]);
1400 }
1401 for (const auto &reg : reuse_regions[d]) {
1402 Expr size = box_size(reg.second);
1403 if (!size.defined()) {
1404 total_reuse = Expr();
1405 break;
1406 } else {
1407 total_reuse += size;
1408 }
1409 }
1410 reuse.emplace(dims[d].var, simplify(total_reuse));
1411 }
1412
1413 return reuse;
1414}
1415
1416vector<pair<Partitioner::GroupingChoice, Partitioner::GroupConfig>>
1417Partitioner::choose_candidate_grouping(const vector<pair<string, string>> &cands,
1418 Partitioner::Level level) {
1419 vector<pair<GroupingChoice, GroupConfig>> best_grouping;
1420 Expr best_benefit = make_zero(Int(64));
1421 for (const auto &p : cands) {
1422 // Compute the aggregate benefit of inlining into all the children.
1423 vector<pair<GroupingChoice, GroupConfig>> grouping;
1424
1425 const Function &prod_f = get_element(dep_analysis.env, p.first);
1426 int final_stage = prod_f.updates().size();
1427
1428 FStage prod(prod_f, final_stage);
1429
1430 for (const FStage &c : get_element(children, prod)) {
1431 GroupConfig best_config;
1432 GroupingChoice cand_choice(prod_f.name(), c);
1433
1434 // Check if the candidate has been evaluated for grouping before
1435 const auto &iter = grouping_cache.find(cand_choice);
1436 if (iter != grouping_cache.end()) {
1437 best_config = iter->second;
1438 } else {
1439 best_config = evaluate_choice(cand_choice, level);
1440 // Cache the result of the evaluation for the pair
1441 grouping_cache.emplace(cand_choice, best_config);
1442 }
1443
1444 grouping.emplace_back(cand_choice, best_config);
1445 }
1446
1447 bool no_redundant_work = false;
1448 Expr overall_benefit = estimate_benefit(grouping, no_redundant_work, true);
1449
1450 debug(3) << "Candidate grouping:\n";
1451 for (const auto &g : grouping) {
1452 debug(3) << " " << g.first;
1453 }
1454 debug(3) << "Candidate benefit: " << overall_benefit << "\n";
1455 // TODO: The grouping process can be non-deterministic when the costs
1456 // of two choices are equal
1457 if (overall_benefit.defined() && can_prove(best_benefit < overall_benefit)) {
1458 best_grouping = grouping;
1459 best_benefit = overall_benefit;
1460 }
1461 }
1462
1463 debug(3) << "\nBest grouping:\n";
1464 for (const auto &g : best_grouping) {
1465 debug(3) << " " << g.first;
1466 }
1467 if (!best_grouping.empty()) {
1468 debug(3) << "Best benefit: " << best_benefit << "\n";
1469 }
1470
1471 return best_grouping;
1472}
1473
1474inline bool operator==(const map<string, Expr> &m1, const map<string, Expr> &m2) {
1475 if (m1.size() != m2.size()) {
1476 return false;
1477 }
1478 for (const auto &it1 : m1) {
1479 const auto &it2 = m2.find(it1.first);
1480 if (it2 == m2.end()) {
1481 return false;
1482 } else if (!equal(it1.second, it2->second)) {
1483 return false;
1484 }
1485 }
1486 return true;
1487}
1488
1489vector<map<string, Expr>> Partitioner::generate_tile_configs(const FStage &stg) {
1490 // TODO: This is a wart due to the cost model not taking vectorization
1491 // and pre-fetching into account. Ensuring the innermost dimension has
1492 // at least size of 64 gives enough values for vectorization and can help
1493 // with prefetching. This also interacts with the number of parallel tasks
1494 // that are generated.
1495 int min_inner_dim_size = 64;
1496
1497 const vector<Dim> &dims = get_stage_dims(stg.func, stg.stage_num);
1498
1499 // Get the dimensions that are going to be tiled in this stage.
1500 // Skipping rvars for now.
1501 vector<string> tile_vars;
1502 for (int d = 0; d < (int)dims.size() - 1; d++) {
1503 if (!dims[d].is_rvar()) {
1504 tile_vars.push_back(dims[d].var);
1505 }
1506 }
1507
1508 vector<int> size_variants = {1, 4, 8, 16, 32, 64, 128, 256};
1509 vector<map<string, Expr>> tile_configs;
1510
1511 // For all the tile configurations generated, we force the innermost dimension
1512 // to be at least of size 64 to ensure enough values for vectorization.
1513
1514 // Skewed tile configurations
1515 for (size_t i = 0; i < tile_vars.size(); i++) {
1516 for (const auto &dim_size : size_variants) {
1517 map<string, Expr> tiling;
1518 tiling.emplace(tile_vars[i],
1519 (i == 0) ? std::max(dim_size, min_inner_dim_size) : dim_size);
1520 for (size_t j = 0; j < tile_vars.size(); j++) {
1521 if (j < i) {
1522 tiling.emplace(tile_vars[j], size_variants[size_variants.size() - 1]);
1523 } else if (j > i) {
1524 tiling.emplace(tile_vars[j], size_variants[0]);
1525 }
1526 }
1527 if (!tiling.empty()) {
1528 bool is_duplicate =
1529 std::find_if(tile_configs.begin(), tile_configs.end(),
1530 [&tiling](const map<string, Expr> &m) { return (tiling == m); }) != tile_configs.end();
1531 if (!is_duplicate) {
1532 tile_configs.push_back(tiling);
1533 }
1534 }
1535 }
1536 }
1537
1538 // Almost square tile configurations
1539 for (const auto &dim_size : size_variants) {
1540 map<string, Expr> tiling;
1541 for (size_t j = 0; j < tile_vars.size(); j++) {
1542 tiling.emplace(tile_vars[j],
1543 (j == 0) ? std::max(dim_size, min_inner_dim_size) : dim_size);
1544 }
1545 if (!tiling.empty()) {
1546 bool is_duplicate =
1547 std::find_if(tile_configs.begin(), tile_configs.end(),
1548 [&tiling](const map<string, Expr> &m) { return (tiling == m); }) != tile_configs.end();
1549 if (!is_duplicate) {
1550 tile_configs.push_back(tiling);
1551 }
1552 }
1553 }
1554
1555 // Reorder tile configurations
1556 for (int i = 0; i < (1 << (tile_vars.size())); i++) {
1557 map<string, Expr> tiling;
1558 for (size_t j = 0; j < tile_vars.size(); j++) {
1559 if (((i >> (j)) & 1) == 1) {
1560 if (j == 0) {
1561 tiling.emplace(tile_vars[j], min_inner_dim_size);
1562 } else {
1563 tiling.emplace(tile_vars[j], 1);
1564 }
1565 }
1566 }
1567 if (!tiling.empty()) {
1568 bool is_duplicate =
1569 std::find_if(tile_configs.begin(), tile_configs.end(),
1570 [&tiling](const map<string, Expr> &m) { return (tiling == m); }) != tile_configs.end();
1571 if (!is_duplicate) {
1572 tile_configs.push_back(tiling);
1573 }
1574 }
1575 }
1576
1577 return tile_configs;
1578}
1579
1580pair<map<string, Expr>, Partitioner::GroupAnalysis>
1581Partitioner::find_best_tile_config(const Group &g) {
1582 // Initialize to no tiling
1583 map<string, Expr> no_tile_config;
1584 Group no_tile = g;
1585 no_tile.tile_sizes = no_tile_config;
1586
1587 bool show_analysis = false;
1588 GroupAnalysis no_tile_analysis = analyze_group(no_tile, show_analysis);
1589
1590 GroupAnalysis best_analysis = no_tile_analysis;
1591 map<string, Expr> best_config = no_tile_config;
1592 if (!best_analysis.cost.defined()) {
1593 return make_pair(best_config, best_analysis);
1594 }
1595
1596 // Generate tiling configurations
1597 vector<map<string, Expr>> configs = generate_tile_configs(g.output);
1598
1599 Group best_group = g;
1600 for (const auto &config : configs) {
1601 Group new_group = g;
1602 new_group.tile_sizes = config;
1603
1604 GroupAnalysis new_analysis = analyze_group(new_group, show_analysis);
1605
1606 bool no_redundant_work = false;
1607 Expr benefit = estimate_benefit(best_analysis, new_analysis,
1608 no_redundant_work, true);
1609
1610 if (show_analysis) {
1611 debug(0) << "Benefit relative to not tiling:" << benefit << "\n";
1612 debug(0) << "Best analysis:" << new_analysis;
1613 debug(0) << "No tile analysis:" << no_tile_analysis;
1614 debug(0)
1615 << "arith cost:" << cast<float>(new_analysis.cost.arith / no_tile_analysis.cost.arith)
1616 << ", mem cost:" << cast<float>(new_analysis.cost.memory / no_tile_analysis.cost.memory) << "\n";
1617 }
1618
1619 if (benefit.defined() && can_prove(benefit > 0)) {
1620 best_config = config;
1621 best_analysis = new_analysis;
1622 best_group = new_group;
1623 }
1624 }
1625
1626 return make_pair(best_config, best_analysis);
1627}
1628
1629void Partitioner::group(Partitioner::Level level) {
1630 bool fixpoint = false;
1631 while (!fixpoint) {
1632 Cost pre_merge = get_pipeline_cost();
1633
1634 fixpoint = true;
1635 vector<pair<string, string>> cand;
1636 for (const pair<const FStage, Group> &g : groups) {
1637 bool is_output = false;
1638 for (const Function &f : outputs) {
1639 if (g.first.func.name() == f.name()) {
1640 is_output = true;
1641 break;
1642 }
1643 }
1644
1645 // All stages of a function are computed at a single location.
1646 // The last stage of the function represents the candidate choice
1647 // of grouping the function into a consumer.
1648
1649 const Function &prod_f = get_element(dep_analysis.env, g.first.func.name());
1650 bool is_final_stage = (g.first.stage_num == prod_f.updates().size());
1651
1652 if (is_output || !is_final_stage) {
1653 continue;
1654 }
1655
1656 const auto &iter = children.find(g.first);
1657 if (iter != children.end()) {
1658 // All the stages belonging to a function are considered to be a
1659 // single child.
1660 set<string> child_groups;
1661 for (const FStage &s : iter->second) {
1662 child_groups.insert(s.func.name());
1663 }
1664
1665 int num_children = child_groups.size();
1666 // Only groups with a single child are considered for grouping
1667 // when grouping for computing in tiles.
1668 // TODO: The current scheduling model does not allow functions
1669 // to be computed at different points.
1670 if ((num_children == 1) && (level == Partitioner::Level::FastMem)) {
1671 const string &prod_name = prod_f.name();
1672 const string &cons_name = (*child_groups.begin());
1673 cand.emplace_back(prod_name, cons_name);
1674 } else if ((level == Partitioner::Level::Inline) && prod_f.is_pure()) {
1675 const string &prod_name = prod_f.name();
1676 cand.emplace_back(prod_name, "");
1677 }
1678 }
1679 }
1680
1681 debug(3) << "\n============================\n"
1682 << "Current grouping candidates:\n"
1683 << "============================\n";
1684 for (size_t i = 0; i < cand.size(); ++i) {
1685 debug(3) << "{" << cand[i].first << ", " << cand[i].second << "}\n";
1686 }
1687
1688 vector<pair<GroupingChoice, GroupConfig>> best = choose_candidate_grouping(cand, level);
1689 if (best.empty()) {
1690 continue;
1691 } else {
1692 fixpoint = false;
1693 }
1694
1695 // The following code makes the assumption that all the stages of a function
1696 // will be in the same group. 'choose_candidate_grouping' ensures that the
1697 // grouping choice being returned adheres to this constraint.
1698 const string &prod = best[0].first.prod;
1699
1700 const Function &prod_f = get_element(dep_analysis.env, prod);
1701 size_t num_stages = prod_f.updates().size() + 1;
1702
1703 FStage final_stage(prod_f, num_stages - 1);
1704 set<FStage> prod_group_children = get_element(children, final_stage);
1705
1706 // Invalidate entries of the grouping cache
1707 set<GroupingChoice> invalid_keys;
1708 for (const auto &c : prod_group_children) {
1709 for (const auto &entry : grouping_cache) {
1710 if ((entry.first.prod == c.func.name()) || (entry.first.cons == c)) {
1711 invalid_keys.insert(entry.first);
1712 }
1713 }
1714 }
1715 for (const auto &key : invalid_keys) {
1716 grouping_cache.erase(key);
1717 }
1718
1719 for (const auto &group : best) {
1720 internal_assert(group.first.prod == prod);
1721 merge_groups(group.first, group.second, level);
1722 }
1723
1724 for (size_t s = 0; s < num_stages; s++) {
1725 FStage prod_group(prod_f, s);
1726 groups.erase(prod_group);
1727 group_costs.erase(prod_group);
1728
1729 // Update the children mapping
1730 children.erase(prod_group);
1731 for (auto &f : children) {
1732 set<FStage> &cons = f.second;
1733 auto iter = cons.find(prod_group);
1734 if (iter != cons.end()) {
1735 cons.erase(iter);
1736 // For a function with multiple stages, all the stages will
1737 // be in the same group and the consumers of the function
1738 // only depend on the last stage. Therefore, when the
1739 // producer group has multiple stages, parents of the
1740 // producers should point to the consumers of the last
1741 // stage of the producer.
1742 cons.insert(prod_group_children.begin(), prod_group_children.end());
1743 }
1744 }
1745 }
1746
1747 Cost post_merge = get_pipeline_cost();
1748 if (debug::debug_level() >= 3) {
1749 disp_pipeline_costs();
1750 }
1751 }
1752}
1753
1754DimBounds Partitioner::get_bounds(const FStage &s) {
1755 DimBounds bounds;
1756
1757 const vector<string> &args = s.func.args();
1758 for (size_t d = 0; d < args.size(); d++) {
1759 bounds[args[d]] = get_element(pipeline_bounds, s.func.name())[d];
1760 }
1761
1762 return get_stage_bounds(s.func, s.stage_num, bounds);
1763}
1764
1765DimBounds Partitioner::get_bounds_from_tile_sizes(const FStage &s,
1766 const map<string, Expr> &tile_sizes) {
1767 map<string, Interval> bounds;
1768
1769 const map<string, Interval> &def_bounds = get_bounds(s);
1770 const vector<Dim> &dims = get_stage_dims(s.func, s.stage_num);
1771
1772 for (int d = 0; d < (int)dims.size() - 1; d++) {
1773 string var = dims[d].var;
1774 const Interval &bound = get_element(def_bounds, var);
1775 const auto &iter = tile_sizes.find(var);
1776 if (iter != tile_sizes.end()) {
1777 const Expr &size = iter->second;
1778 // Check if the bounds allow for tiling with the given tile size,
1779 // i.e. ensure at least 2 tiles
1780 Expr extent = get_extent(bound);
1781 internal_assert(extent.defined());
1782 if (can_prove(extent >= 2 * size)) {
1783 // TODO: Maybe shift this to the center of the pipeline bound
1784 bounds[var] = Interval(0, simplify(size - 1));
1785 } else {
1786 // If the dimension is too small, do not tile it and set the
1787 // extent of the bounds to that of the dimension estimate
1788 bounds[var] = bound;
1789 }
1790 } else {
1791 bounds[var] = bound;
1792 }
1793 }
1794
1795 return bounds;
1796}
1797
1798Partitioner::GroupAnalysis Partitioner::analyze_group(const Group &g, bool show_analysis) {
1799 set<string> group_inputs;
1800 set<string> group_members;
1801
1802 for (const auto &stg : g.members) {
1803 group_members.insert(stg.func.name());
1804 set<string> parents = get_parents(stg.func, stg.stage_num);
1805 for (const auto &c : parents) {
1806 bool is_member = false;
1807 for (const auto &m : g.members) {
1808 if (m.func.name() == c) {
1809 is_member = true;
1810 break;
1811 }
1812 }
1813 if (!is_member) {
1814 group_inputs.insert(c);
1815 }
1816 }
1817 }
1818
1819 // Count the number of tiles
1820 Expr estimate_tiles = make_one(Int(64));
1821 Expr parallelism = make_one(Int(64));
1822
1823 if (!g.output.func.has_extern_definition()) {
1824 // Get the definition corresponding to the group output
1825 Definition def = get_stage_definition(g.output.func, g.output.stage_num);
1826 const vector<Dim> &dims = def.schedule().dims();
1827
1828 DimBounds stg_bounds = get_bounds(g.output);
1829
1830 for (int d = 0; d < (int)dims.size() - 1; d++) {
1831 const string &var = dims[d].var;
1832 const auto &iter = g.tile_sizes.find(var);
1833 if (iter != g.tile_sizes.end()) {
1834 const Expr &size = iter->second;
1835 Expr extent = get_extent(get_element(stg_bounds, var));
1836 if (!extent.defined()) {
1837 return GroupAnalysis();
1838 }
1839
1840 Expr dim_tiles = simplify((extent + size - 1) / size);
1841 estimate_tiles *= dim_tiles;
1842 // Since all Vars are inherently parallelizable by construct, we
1843 // only need to take RVars into account for the analysis.
1844 if (can_parallelize_rvar(var, g.output.func.name(), def)) {
1845 parallelism *= dim_tiles;
1846 }
1847 }
1848 }
1849 }
1850
1851 // Get the regions of the pipeline required to compute a tile of the group
1852 DimBounds tile_bounds = get_bounds_from_tile_sizes(g.output, g.tile_sizes);
1853
1854 map<string, Box> alloc_regions = dep_analysis.regions_required(
1855 g.output.func, g.output.stage_num, tile_bounds, group_members, false, &costs.input_estimates);
1856
1857 map<string, Box> compute_regions = dep_analysis.regions_required(
1858 g.output.func, g.output.stage_num, tile_bounds, group_members, true, &costs.input_estimates);
1859
1860 map<string, Box> group_reg, prod_reg, input_reg;
1861
1862 // Separating into regions that computed within the group and regions that
1863 // are input to the group
1864 for (const auto &reg : compute_regions) {
1865 if ((group_members.find(reg.first) != group_members.end()) &&
1866 (reg.first != g.output.func.name())) {
1867 group_reg.emplace(reg.first, reg.second);
1868 } else if (group_inputs.find(reg.first) != group_inputs.end()) {
1869 if (dep_analysis.env.find(reg.first) != dep_analysis.env.end()) {
1870 prod_reg.emplace(reg.first, reg.second);
1871 } else {
1872 input_reg.emplace(reg.first, reg.second);
1873 }
1874 }
1875 }
1876
1877 // Aggregate costs for intermediate functions in a tile and the
1878 // tile output
1879 Cost tile_cost = costs.region_cost(group_reg, g.inlined);
1880 if (!tile_cost.defined()) {
1881 return GroupAnalysis();
1882 }
1883
1884 Cost out_cost = costs.stage_region_cost(g.output.func.name(),
1885 g.output.stage_num,
1886 tile_bounds, g.inlined);
1887 if (!out_cost.defined()) {
1888 return GroupAnalysis();
1889 }
1890
1891 for (const auto &reg : alloc_regions) {
1892 if (!box_size(reg.second).defined()) {
1893 return GroupAnalysis();
1894 }
1895 }
1896
1897 Cost group_cost(simplify(tile_cost.arith + out_cost.arith),
1898 simplify(tile_cost.memory + out_cost.memory));
1899
1900 // Detailed load costs for all the group intermediates
1901 map<string, Expr> group_load_costs =
1902 costs.detailed_load_costs(group_reg, g.inlined);
1903
1904 map<string, Expr> out_load_costs =
1905 costs.stage_detailed_load_costs(g.output.func.name(),
1906 g.output.stage_num,
1907 tile_bounds, g.inlined);
1908
1909 combine_load_costs(group_load_costs, out_load_costs);
1910
1911 Box out_tile_extent;
1912 if (g.output.stage_num == 0) {
1913 const vector<string> &args = g.output.func.args();
1914 for (size_t d = 0; d < args.size(); d++) {
1915 const auto &iter = tile_bounds.find(args[d]);
1916 if (iter != tile_bounds.end()) {
1917 out_tile_extent.push_back(iter->second);
1918 } else {
1919 out_tile_extent.push_back(Interval());
1920 }
1921 }
1922 }
1923
1924 Cost per_tile_cost(group_cost.arith, make_zero(Int(64)));
1925
1926 // This is the old cost model; keeping it here for reference, for now.
1927 /*
1928 if (tile_inter_size > arch_params.l1_size) {
1929 // Conservative estimate of accesses to memory
1930 //per_tile_mem_cost = tile_inter_size;
1931 // Aggressive estimate of accesses to memory
1932 per_tile_mem_cost = tile_cost.second;
1933 } else {
1934 // The tile_input_size captures the region of the input
1935 // required to compute the tile. However, all of it many not be
1936 // accessed during the computation of the tile when the access
1937 // is sparse. A better estimate is given by the smaller of
1938 // the number of memory accesses and the region size
1939 per_tile_mem_cost = std::min(tile_input_size + tile_output_size,
1940 tile_cost.second);
1941 }*/
1942
1943 // TODO: Use smooth step curve from Jon to better model cache behavior,
1944 // where each step corresponds to different cache level.
1945 //
1946 // The current cost model drops off linearly. Larger memory footprint is
1947 // penalized more than smaller memory footprint (since smaller one can fit
1948 // more in the cache). The cost is clamped at 'balance', which is roughly at
1949 // memory footprint equal to or larger than the last level cache size.
1950
1951 // If 'model_reuse' is set, the cost model should take into account memory
1952 // reuse within the tile, e.g. matrix multiply reuses inputs multiple times.
1953 // TODO: Implement a better reuse model.
1954 bool model_reuse = false;
1955
1956 // Linear dropoff
1957 float load_slope = arch_params.balance / arch_params.last_level_cache_size;
1958 for (const auto &f_load : group_load_costs) {
1959 internal_assert(g.inlined.find(f_load.first) == g.inlined.end())
1960 << "Intermediates of inlined pure function \"" << f_load.first
1961 << "\" should not have been in the group_load_costs\n";
1962
1963 const auto &alloc_reg = get_element(alloc_regions, f_load.first);
1964
1965 Expr footprint;
1966 bool is_group_member = (group_members.find(f_load.first) != group_members.end());
1967 bool is_output = (f_load.first == g.output.func.name());
1968
1969 // We use allocated region as conservative estimate of the footprint since
1970 // the loads could be from any random locations of the allocated regions.
1971
1972 if (!is_output && is_group_member) {
1973 footprint = costs.region_size(f_load.first, alloc_reg);
1974 } else {
1975 Expr initial_footprint;
1976 const auto &f_load_pipeline_bounds = get_element(pipeline_bounds, f_load.first);
1977
1978 bool is_function = (dep_analysis.env.find(f_load.first) != dep_analysis.env.end());
1979 if (!is_function) { // It is a load to some input buffer
1980 // Initial loads
1981 initial_footprint = costs.input_region_size(f_load.first, f_load_pipeline_bounds);
1982 // Subsequent loads
1983 footprint = costs.input_region_size(f_load.first, alloc_reg);
1984 } else if (is_output) { // Load to the output function of the group
1985 internal_assert(is_group_member)
1986 << "Output " << f_load.first << " should have been a group member\n";
1987 // Initial loads
1988 initial_footprint = costs.region_size(f_load.first, f_load_pipeline_bounds);
1989 // Subsequent loads
1990 footprint = costs.region_size(f_load.first, out_tile_extent);
1991 } else { // Load to some non-member function (i.e. function from other groups)
1992 // Initial loads
1993 initial_footprint = costs.region_size(f_load.first, f_load_pipeline_bounds);
1994 // Subsequent loads
1995 footprint = costs.region_size(f_load.first, alloc_reg);
1996 }
1997
1998 if (model_reuse) {
1999 Expr initial_factor =
2000 cast<int64_t>(min(1 + initial_footprint * load_slope, arch_params.balance));
2001 per_tile_cost.memory += initial_factor * footprint;
2002 } else {
2003 footprint = initial_footprint;
2004 }
2005
2006 if (!footprint.defined()) {
2007 return GroupAnalysis();
2008 }
2009 }
2010
2011 Expr cost_factor = cast<int64_t>(min(1 + footprint * load_slope, arch_params.balance));
2012 per_tile_cost.memory += cost_factor * f_load.second;
2013 }
2014
2015 if (show_analysis) {
2016 debug(0) << "\nDetailed loads:\n";
2017 for (const auto &f_load : group_load_costs) {
2018 debug(0) << "(" << f_load.first << "," << f_load.second << ")";
2019 }
2020 debug(0) << "\n";
2021
2022 debug(0) << "\nPer tile memory cost:" << per_tile_cost.memory << "\n";
2023 debug(0) << "Per tile arith cost:" << per_tile_cost.arith << "\n";
2024 }
2025
2026 GroupAnalysis g_analysis(
2027 Cost(per_tile_cost.arith * estimate_tiles, per_tile_cost.memory * estimate_tiles),
2028 parallelism);
2029 g_analysis.simplify();
2030
2031 return g_analysis;
2032}

2034Partitioner::Group Partitioner::merge_groups(const Group &prod_group,
2035 const Group &cons_group) {
2036 vector<FStage> group_members;
2037 for (const auto &s : prod_group.members) {
2038 group_members.push_back(s);
2039 }
2040 for (const auto &s : cons_group.members) {
2041 group_members.push_back(s);
2042 }
2043
2044 Group group(cons_group.output, group_members);
2045
2046 for (const auto &f : prod_group.inlined) {
2047 group.inlined.insert(f);
2048 }
2049 for (const auto &f : cons_group.inlined) {
2050 group.inlined.insert(f);
2051 }
2052
2053 return group;
2054}
2055
2056void Partitioner::merge_groups(const GroupingChoice &choice, const GroupConfig &eval,
2057 Partitioner::Level level) {
2058 const Function &prod_f = get_element(dep_analysis.env, choice.prod);
2059 size_t num_stages = prod_f.updates().size() + 1;
2060
2061 const FStage &child = choice.cons;
2062 Group &child_group = get_element(groups, child);
2063
2064 for (size_t s = 0; s < num_stages; s++) {
2065 FStage cand(prod_f, s);
2066 Group &cand_group = get_element(groups, cand);
2067 child_group.members.insert(child_group.members.end(),
2068 cand_group.members.begin(),
2069 cand_group.members.end());
2070
2071 if (level == Partitioner::Level::Inline) {
2072 for (const auto &stg : cand_group.members) {
2073 child_group.inlined.insert(stg.func.name());
2074 }
2075 } else {
2076 for (const auto &in : cand_group.inlined) {
2077 child_group.inlined.insert(in);
2078 }
2079 }
2080 }
2081
2082 child_group.tile_sizes = eval.tile_sizes;
2083
2084 // Update group costs.
2085 // We could just reuse the analysis from 'eval' since it was computed
2086 // by assuming the merge had happened.
2087 group_costs[child] = eval.analysis;
2088}
2089
2090Partitioner::GroupConfig Partitioner::evaluate_choice(const GroupingChoice &choice,
2091 Partitioner::Level level) {
2092 // Create a group that reflects the grouping choice and evaluate the cost
2093 // of the group.
2094 const Function &prod_f = get_element(dep_analysis.env, choice.prod);
2095 int num_prod_stages = prod_f.updates().size() + 1;
2096 vector<Group> prod_groups;
2097
2098 for (int s = 0; s < num_prod_stages; s++) {
2099 FStage prod_s(prod_f, s);
2100 prod_groups.push_back(get_element(groups, prod_s));
2101 }
2102
2103 Group cons = get_element(groups, choice.cons);
2104 Group group = cons;
2105 for (const auto &prod_g : prod_groups) {
2106 group = merge_groups(prod_g, group);
2107 }
2108
2109 GroupAnalysis group_analysis;
2110 map<string, Expr> best_tile_config;
2111
2112 if (level == Partitioner::Level::Inline) {
2113 // Set the tile sizes to one along all dimensions of the consumer group
2114 map<string, Expr> tile_sizes;
2115
2116 const Function &cons_f = cons.output.func;
2117
2118 const vector<Dim> &dims = get_stage_dims(cons_f, cons.output.stage_num);
2119 for (int d = 0; d < (int)dims.size() - 1; d++) {
2120 tile_sizes[dims[d].var] = 1;
2121 }
2122
2123 group.tile_sizes = tile_sizes;
2124
2125 for (const auto &prod_g : prod_groups) {
2126 for (const FStage &s : prod_g.members) {
2127 group.inlined.insert(s.func.name());
2128 }
2129 }
2130
2131 for (const string &f : cons.inlined) {
2132 group.inlined.insert(f);
2133 }
2134
2135 group_analysis = analyze_group(group, false);
2136 best_tile_config = tile_sizes;
2137
2138 } else {
2139 pair<map<string, Expr>, GroupAnalysis> config = find_best_tile_config(group);
2140 best_tile_config = config.first;
2141 group_analysis = config.second;
2142 }
2143
2144 return GroupConfig(best_tile_config, group_analysis);
2145}
2146
2147Expr Partitioner::estimate_benefit(const GroupAnalysis &old_grouping,
2148 const GroupAnalysis &new_grouping,
2149 bool no_redundant_work,
2150 bool ensure_parallelism) const {
2151 // TODO: Instead of having a hard parallelism constraint, it may be better
2152 // to consider other metric, such as arith_cost/parallelism
2153 if (ensure_parallelism &&
2154 (!new_grouping.parallelism.defined() ||
2155 !can_prove(new_grouping.parallelism >= arch_params.parallelism))) {
2156 return Expr();
2157 }
2158
2159 if (!old_grouping.cost.defined() || !new_grouping.cost.defined()) {
2160 return Expr();
2161 }
2162
2163 Expr arith_benefit = old_grouping.cost.arith - new_grouping.cost.arith;
2164 if (no_redundant_work && !can_prove(arith_benefit >= 0)) {
2165 return Expr();
2166 }
2167 Expr mem_benefit = old_grouping.cost.memory - new_grouping.cost.memory;
2168 return simplify(mem_benefit + arith_benefit);
2169}
2170
2171Expr Partitioner::estimate_benefit(
2172 const vector<pair<GroupingChoice, GroupConfig>> &new_grouping,
2173 bool no_redundant_work, bool ensure_parallelism) const {
2174
2175 set<FStage> old_groups;
2176
2177 GroupAnalysis new_group_analysis(Cost(0, 0), Int(64).max());
2178 for (const auto &g : new_grouping) {
2179 const Function &prod_f = get_element(dep_analysis.env, g.first.prod);
2180 int num_prod_stages = prod_f.updates().size() + 1;
2181 for (int s = 0; s < num_prod_stages; s++) {
2182 FStage prod_s(prod_f, s);
2183 old_groups.insert(prod_s);
2184 }
2185
2186 old_groups.insert(g.first.cons);
2187
2188 GroupAnalysis analysisg = g.second.analysis;
2189 if (analysisg.defined()) {
2190 new_group_analysis.cost.arith += analysisg.cost.arith;
2191 new_group_analysis.cost.memory += analysisg.cost.memory;
2192 new_group_analysis.parallelism = min(new_group_analysis.parallelism,
2193 analysisg.parallelism);
2194 } else {
2195 new_group_analysis.cost = Cost();
2196 new_group_analysis.parallelism = Expr();
2197 break;
2198 }
2199 }
2200 new_group_analysis.simplify();
2201
2202 GroupAnalysis old_group_analysis(Cost(0, 0), Int(64).max());
2203 for (const auto &g : old_groups) {
2204 const auto &iter = group_costs.find(g);
2205 internal_assert(iter != group_costs.end());
2206 GroupAnalysis analysisg = iter->second;
2207 if (analysisg.defined()) {
2208 old_group_analysis.cost.arith += analysisg.cost.arith;
2209 old_group_analysis.cost.memory += analysisg.cost.memory;
2210 old_group_analysis.parallelism = min(old_group_analysis.parallelism,
2211 analysisg.parallelism);
2212 } else {
2213 old_group_analysis.cost = Cost();
2214 old_group_analysis.parallelism = Expr();
2215 break;
2216 }
2217 }
2218 old_group_analysis.simplify();
2219
2220 return estimate_benefit(old_group_analysis, new_group_analysis,
2221 no_redundant_work, ensure_parallelism);
2222}

2232map<FStage, map<string, Box>> Partitioner::group_storage_bounds() {
2233 map<FStage, map<string, Box>> group_storage_bounds;
2234 for (const pair<const FStage, Group> &gpair : groups) {
2235 const Group &g = gpair.second;
2236 DimBounds bounds = get_bounds_from_tile_sizes(g.output, g.tile_sizes);
2237
2238 set<string> prods;
2239 for (const FStage &s : g.members) {
2240 prods.insert(s.func.name());
2241 }
2242

2244 dep_analysis.regions_required(g.output.func, g.output.stage_num,
2245 bounds, prods, false, &costs.input_estimates);

2247 for (const FStage &s : g.members) {
2248 const auto &iter = reg_alloc.find(s.func.name());
2249 if ((iter != reg_alloc.end()) && (s.func.name() != g.output.func.name())) {
2250 group_alloc[s.func.name()] = iter->second;
2251 }

2254 group_storage_bounds[gpair.first] = group_alloc;
2255 }
