2294
2295// We need to get the base name of the dimension for scheduling (i.e. it
2296// can't have any dots). For example, in split case, if "x" is the starting
2297// dimension name, after split(x, x0, xi, ...), we will end up with something
2298// like "x.x0" and "x.xi". If we want to later schedule "x.x0", we need to
2299// pass "x0" instead of "x.x0".
2300string get_base_name(string name) {
2301 size_t dot_pos = name.rfind('.');
2302 if (dot_pos != string::npos) {
2303 return name.substr(dot_pos + 1);
2304 }
2305 return name;
2306}
2307
2308pair<VarOrRVar, VarOrRVar> Partitioner::split_dim(
2309 const Group &g, Stage f_handle, int stage_num, const Definition &def,
2310 bool is_group_output, const VarOrRVar &v, const Expr &factor, const string &in_suffix,
2311 const string &out_suffix, map<string, Expr> &estimates, AutoSchedule &sched) {
2312 // Create new variables for the split dimensions
2313 string arg_name = v.name();
2314 string inner_name = arg_name + in_suffix;
2315 string outer_name = arg_name + out_suffix;
2316 VarOrRVar inner(inner_name, v.is_rvar), outer(outer_name, v.is_rvar);
2317
2318 {
2319 const auto &iter = sched.internal_vars.find(inner.name());
2320 if (iter == sched.internal_vars.end()) {
2321 sched.internal_vars.emplace(inner.name(), inner);
2322 } else {
2323 internal_assert(iter->second.is_rvar == inner.is_rvar);
2324 }
2325 }
2326 {
2327 const auto &iter = sched.internal_vars.find(outer.name());
2328 if (iter == sched.internal_vars.end()) {
2329 sched.internal_vars.emplace(outer.name(), outer);
2330 } else {
2331 internal_assert(iter->second.is_rvar == outer.is_rvar);
2332 }
2333 }
2334
2335 // The default tail strategy is good enough for most use cases (see docs on
2336 // TailStrategy::Auto). However, the default of pure vars in update definitions
2337 // is RoundUp, which may introduces an out-of-bound error if it is an access
2338 // to inputs or outputs.
2339 //
2340 // We could have just used GuardWithIf when splitting pure vars in update
2341 // definition to ensure no out-of-bounds error. However, this is only
2342 // necessary, if the update definition involves accesses to inputs or outputs.
2343 // For other accesses, we could potentially use a more aggressive tail strategy
2344 // such as RoundUp or ShiftInwards. Note that if we use RoundUp or ShiftInwards,
2345 // any nested loops (generated by compute_at) will be affected as well. However,
2346 // since in the current auto-scheduler model, we always compute_at at the group
2347 // output, if the update definition is not the group output, we do not need to
2348 // care for the nested loops. If it is the update definition of the group output
2349 // however, we'd better make sure that no other member of the groups accesses
2350 // the inputs or outputs.
2351
2352 TailStrategy strategy = TailStrategy::Auto;
2353 if ((stage_num > 0) && !v.is_rvar) {
2354 // TODO: It's safe to use RoundUp here if we know there are no
2355 // loads from any input, but at this point we've lost track of
2356 // loads from inputs that happen inside inlined Funcs.
2357 strategy = TailStrategy::GuardWithIf;
2358 }
2359
2360 f_handle.split(v, outer, inner, factor, strategy);
2361
2362 std::ostringstream oss;
2363 oss << "split(" << arg_name << ", " << outer_name << ", " << inner_name << ", " << factor;
2364 switch (strategy) {
2365 case TailStrategy::RoundUp:
2366 oss << ", TailStrategy::RoundUp)";
2367 break;
2368 case TailStrategy::GuardWithIf:
2369 oss << ", TailStrategy::GuardWithIf)";
2370 break;
2371 case TailStrategy::ShiftInwards:
2372 oss << ", TailStrategy::ShiftInwards)";
2373 break;
2374 case TailStrategy::Auto:
2375 oss << ")";
2376 break;
2377 default:
2378 internal_error;
2379 }
2380 sched.push_schedule(f_handle.name(), stage_num, oss.str(),
2381 {arg_name, outer_name, inner_name});
2382
2383 const Expr &est = get_element(estimates, arg_name);
2384 internal_assert(est.defined());
2385
2386 estimates[inner_name] = factor;
2387 estimates[outer_name] = simplify((est + factor - 1) / factor);
2388 estimates.erase(arg_name);
2389
2390 return make_pair(inner, outer);
2391}
2392
2393void Partitioner::vectorize_stage(const Group &g, Stage f_handle, int stage_num,
2394 Definition def, const Function &func, bool is_group_output,
2395 const Target &t, set<string> &rvars,
2396 map<string, Expr> &estimates, AutoSchedule &sched) {
2397 vector<Dim> &dims = def.schedule().dims();
2398 int vec_dim_index = -1;
2399
2400 // Set the vector length as the maximum of the natural vector size of all
2401 // values produced by the function.
2402 int vec_len = 0;
2403 for (const auto &type : func.output_types()) {
2404 vec_len = std::max(vec_len, t.natural_vector_size(type));
2405 }
2406
2407 for (int d = 0; d < (int)dims.size() - 1; d++) {
2408 string dim_name = get_base_name(dims[d].var);
2409 bool can_vectorize = true;
2410 if (rvars.find(dim_name) != rvars.end()) {
2411 can_vectorize = can_parallelize_rvar(dim_name, func.name(), def);
2412 }
2413 const auto &iter = estimates.find(dim_name);
2414 if ((iter != estimates.end()) && iter->second.defined()) {
2415 if (can_vectorize && can_prove(iter->second >= vec_len)) {
2416 vec_dim_index = d;
2417 break;
2418 }
2419 }
2420 }
2421
2422 if (vec_dim_index >= 0) {
2423 string vec_dim_name = get_base_name(dims[vec_dim_index].var);
2424 bool is_rvar = (rvars.find(vec_dim_name) != rvars.end());
2425 internal_assert(is_rvar == dims[vec_dim_index].is_rvar());
2426
2427 VarOrRVar vec_var(vec_dim_name, is_rvar);
2428 pair<VarOrRVar, VarOrRVar> split_vars =
2429 split_dim(g, f_handle, stage_num, def, is_group_output, vec_var, vec_len,
2430 "_vi", "_vo", estimates, sched);
2431
2432 f_handle.vectorize(split_vars.first);
2433 sched.push_schedule(f_handle.name(), stage_num,
2434 "vectorize(" + split_vars.first.name() + ")",
2435 {split_vars.first.name()});
2436
2437 if (is_rvar) {
2438 rvars.erase(vec_dim_name);
2439 rvars.insert(split_vars.first.name());
2440 rvars.insert(split_vars.second.name());
2441 }
2442
2443 // TODO: Reorder vector dim to innermost if it is the innermost
2444 // storage dimension of the func.
2445 //
2446 // TODO: Check if the warning is necessary.
2447 if (vec_dim_index > 0) {
2448 user_warning << "Outer dim vectorization of var \"" << vec_dim_name
2449 << "\" in function \"" << f_handle.name() << "\"\n";
2450 }
2451 }
2452}
2453
2454// Return true if the vars/rvars in 'ordering' are in the same order as the
2455// dim list.
2456inline bool operator==(const vector<Dim> &dims, const vector<VarOrRVar> &ordering) {
2457 if (dims.size() != ordering.size() + 1) { // The dim list also contains '__outermost'
2458 return false;
2459 }
2460 for (size_t i = 0; i < ordering.size(); ++i) {
2461 if (dims[i].var != ordering[i].name()) {
2462 return false;
2463 }
2464 }
2465 return true;
2466}
2467
2468// Return true if the vars/rvars in 'ordering' are not in the same order as the
2469// dim list.
2470inline bool operator!=(const vector<Dim> &dims, const vector<VarOrRVar> &ordering) {
2471 return !(dims == ordering);
2472}
2473
2474void Partitioner::reorder_dims(Stage f_handle, int stage_num, Definition def,
2475 map<string, Expr> strides, AutoSchedule &sched) {
2476 vector<Dim> &dims = def.schedule().dims();
2477 internal_assert(dims.size() > 1);
2478 vector<pair<string, int>> order;
2479
2480 for (int d = 0; d < (int)dims.size() - 1; d++) {
2481 internal_assert(strides.find(dims[d].var) != strides.end());
2482 }
2483
2484 // Iterate until all the dimensions have been assigned an order
2485 while (!strides.empty()) {
2486 // Find the pure dimension (can be vars or rvars) with the smallest stride
2487 bool found_pure_dim = false;
2488 Expr min_pure_stride = Int(64).max();
2489 string min_pure_var;
2490 int min_pure_index = -1;
2491 for (int d = 0; d < (int)dims.size() - 1; d++) {
2492 string var_name = get_base_name(dims[d].var);
2493 const auto &iter = strides.find(var_name);
2494 if ((iter != strides.end()) && dims[d].is_pure()) {
2495 const Expr &dim_stride = iter->second;
2496 internal_assert(dim_stride.defined());
2497 if (can_prove(dim_stride < min_pure_stride)) {
2498 min_pure_stride = dim_stride;
2499 min_pure_var = var_name;
2500 min_pure_index = d;
2501 }
2502 found_pure_dim = true;
2503 }
2504 }
2505 if (found_pure_dim && min_pure_var.empty()) {
2506 // Since none of the pure strides can be proven as the minimum, we
2507 // should break here otherwise it may cause infinite loop.
2508 return;
2509 }
2510
2511 // Check if the stride of the pure dimension is smaller than
2512 // the first impure dimension that has not yet been assigned
2513 // an order
2514 Expr min_impure_stride = Int(64).max();
2515 string min_impure_var;
2516 int min_impure_index = -1;
2517 for (int d = 0; d < (int)dims.size() - 1; d++) {
2518 string var_name = get_base_name(dims[d].var);
2519 const auto &iter = strides.find(var_name);
2520 if ((iter != strides.end()) && !dims[d].is_pure()) {
2521 const Expr &dim_stride = iter->second;
2522 internal_assert(dim_stride.defined());
2523 if (can_prove(dim_stride < min_impure_stride)) {
2524 min_impure_stride = dim_stride;
2525 min_impure_var = var_name;
2526 min_impure_index = d;
2527 // Impure dimensions cannot be reordered relative to
2528 // each other. Stop after encountering the first impure
2529 // dimension.
2530 break;
2531 }
2532 }
2533 }
2534
2535 if (min_pure_var.empty() && min_impure_var.empty()) {
2536 // Since none of the pure and impure strides can be proven as the
2537 // minimum, we should break here otherwise it may cause infinite loop.
2538 return;
2539 }
2540
2541 pair<string, int> curr_min_var;
2542 if (!min_impure_var.empty() && can_prove(min_impure_stride < min_pure_stride)) {
2543 curr_min_var.first = min_impure_var;
2544 curr_min_var.second = min_impure_index;
2545 internal_assert(dims[min_impure_index].is_rvar());
2546 } else {
2547 curr_min_var.first = min_pure_var;
2548 curr_min_var.second = min_pure_index;
2549 }
2550
2551 order.push_back(curr_min_var);
2552 strides.erase(curr_min_var.first);
2553 }
2554
2555 vector<VarOrRVar> ordering;
2556 for (const auto &o : order) {
2557 VarOrRVar o_var(o.first, dims[o.second].is_rvar());
2558 ordering.push_back(o_var);
2559 }
2560
2561 internal_assert(!ordering.empty());
2562 set<string> var_list = {ordering[0].name()};
2563 string var_order = ordering[0].name();
2564 for (size_t o = 1; o < ordering.size(); o++) {
2565 var_order += ", " + ordering[o].name();
2566 var_list.insert(ordering[o].name());
2567 }
2568
2569 if (dims != ordering) {
2570 f_handle.reorder(ordering);
2571 sched.push_schedule(f_handle.name(), stage_num, "reorder(" + var_order + ")", var_list);
2572 }
2573}
2574
2575// Visitor to find all the variables the depend on a variable.
2576class FindVarsUsingVar : public IRVisitor {
2577 using IRVisitor::visit;
2578
2579 void visit(const Let *let) override {
2580 if (expr_uses_vars(let->value, vars)) {
2581 vars.push(let->name);
2582 }
2583 let->value.accept(this);
2584 let->body.accept(this);
2585 }
2586
2587public:
2588 Scope<> vars;
2589
2590 FindVarsUsingVar(const string &var) {
2591 vars.push(var);
2592 }
2593};
2594
2595void Partitioner::generate_group_cpu_schedule(
2596 const Group &g, const Target &t,
2597 const map<FStage, DimBounds> &group_loop_bounds,
2598 const map<string, Box> &group_storage_bounds,
2599 const set<string> &inlines,
2600 AutoSchedule &sched) {
2601 string out_f_name = g.output.func.name();
2602 Function g_out = g.output.func;
2603
2604 debug(3) << "\n================\n"
2605 << "Scheduling group:\n"
2606 << "================\n"
2607 << g;
2608
2609 if (g.output.func.has_extern_definition()) {
2610 internal_assert(g.members.size() == 1);
2611 Func(g_out).compute_root();
2612 sched.push_schedule(g_out.name(), g.output.stage_num, "compute_root()", {});
2613 return;
2614 }
2615
2616 // Get the estimates for stage bounds
2617 DimBounds stg_bounds = get_bounds(g.output);
2618 map<string, Expr> stg_estimates = bounds_to_estimates(stg_bounds);
2619
2620 Stage f_handle = Stage(Func(g_out));
2621
2622 // Get a function handle for scheduling the stage
2623 if (g.output.stage_num > 0) {
2624 int stage_num = g.output.stage_num;
2625 f_handle = Func(g_out).update(stage_num - 1);
2626 } else {
2627 Func(g_out).compute_root();
2628 sched.push_schedule(f_handle.name(), g.output.stage_num, "compute_root()", {});
2629 }
2630
2631 // Realize tiling and update the dimension estimates
2632 vector<VarOrRVar> outer_dims;
2633 vector<VarOrRVar> inner_dims;
2634
2635 // Get the definition corresponding to the stage
2636 Definition def = get_stage_definition(g_out, g.output.stage_num);
2637
2638 // 'dims' will get modified since we are going to apply the schedules
2639 // (e.g. tiling, reordering, etc.)
2640 vector<Dim> &dims = def.schedule().dims();
2641
2642 // Keep track of the rvars
2643 set<string> rvars;
2644 for (int d = 0; d < (int)dims.size() - 1; d++) {
2645 if (dims[d].is_rvar()) {
2646 rvars.insert(get_base_name(dims[d].var));
2647 }
2648 }
2649
2650 // Reorder the dimensions for better spatial locality (i.e. smallest stride
2651 // is innermost). If we only have one dimension (excluding __outermost),
2652 // there is nothing to reorder.
2653 if (dims.size() > 2) {
2654 map<string, Expr> strides =
2655 analyze_spatial_locality(g.output, group_storage_bounds, inlines);
2656 if (!strides.empty()) {
2657 reorder_dims(f_handle, g.output.stage_num, def, strides, sched);
2658 }
2659 }
2660
2661 vector<string> dim_vars(dims.size() - 1);
2662 for (int d = 0; d < (int)dims.size() - 1; d++) {
2663 dim_vars[d] = get_base_name(dims[d].var);
2664 }
2665
2666 // Apply tiling to output of the group
2667 for (const auto &var : dim_vars) {
2668 bool is_rvar = (rvars.find(var) != rvars.end());
2669 VarOrRVar v(var, is_rvar);
2670
2671 const auto &iter = g.tile_sizes.find(var);
2672 if ((iter != g.tile_sizes.end()) &&
2673 get_element(stg_estimates, var).defined() &&
2674 can_prove(get_element(stg_estimates, var) > iter->second)) {
2675 const Expr &tile_size = iter->second;
2676 if (can_prove(tile_size == 1)) {
2677 outer_dims.push_back(v);
2678 } else {
2679 pair<VarOrRVar, VarOrRVar> tile_vars =
2680 split_dim(g, f_handle, g.output.stage_num, def, true, v,
2681 tile_size, "_i", "_o", stg_estimates, sched);
2682
2683 inner_dims.push_back(tile_vars.first);
2684 outer_dims.push_back(tile_vars.second);
2685
2686 if (is_rvar) {
2687 rvars.erase(var);
2688 rvars.insert(tile_vars.first.name());
2689 rvars.insert(tile_vars.second.name());
2690 }
2691 }
2692 } else {
2693 inner_dims.push_back(v);
2694 }
2695 }
2696
2697 // Reorder the tile dimensions
2698 if (!outer_dims.empty()) {
2699
2700 vector<VarOrRVar> ordering;
2701 for (const auto &v : inner_dims) {
2702 ordering.push_back(v);
2703 }
2704 for (const auto &v : outer_dims) {
2705 ordering.push_back(v);
2706 }
2707
2708 set<string> var_list;
2709 string var_order = ordering[0].name();
2710 for (size_t o = 1; o < ordering.size(); o++) {
2711 var_order += ", " + ordering[o].name();
2712 var_list.insert(ordering[o].name());
2713 }
2714
2715 if (dims != ordering) {
2716 f_handle.reorder(ordering);
2717 sched.push_schedule(f_handle.name(), g.output.stage_num,
2718 "reorder(" + var_order + ")", var_list);
2719 }
2720 }
2721
2722 vectorize_stage(g, f_handle, g.output.stage_num, def, g_out, true, t,
2723 rvars, stg_estimates, sched);
2724
2725 // Parallelize definition
2726 Expr def_par = 1;
2727 // TODO: Investigate if it is better to pull one large dimension and
2728 // parallelize over it or to generate nested parallelism.
2729 //
2730 // Go from the outer to the innermost loop until sufficient parallelism
2731 // is achieved. Stop the search once we find a vectorized dimension since
2732 // it doesn't make any sense to have a parallelized inner loop within a
2733 // vectorized outer loop.
2734 bool nested_parallelism = true;
2735 if (nested_parallelism) {
2736 int dim_start = dims.size() - 2;
2737 string seq_var;
2738 for (int d = dim_start; d >= 0; d--) {
2739 if (dims[d].for_type == ForType::Vectorized) {
2740 break;
2741 }
2742
2743 string var = get_base_name(dims[d].var);
2744 bool is_rvar = (rvars.find(var) != rvars.end());
2745 internal_assert(is_rvar == dims[d].is_rvar());
2746 VarOrRVar v(var, is_rvar);
2747
2748 if (is_rvar && !can_parallelize_rvar(var, g_out.name(), def)) {
2749 if (seq_var.empty()) {
2750 seq_var = var;
2751 }
2752 continue;
2753 }
2754
2755 if (can_prove(def_par >= arch_params.parallelism)) {
2756 // Enough parallelism to saturate target machine
2757 break;
2758 }
2759
2760 const auto &iter = stg_estimates.find(var);
2761 if ((iter != stg_estimates.end()) && iter->second.defined()) {
2762 if (!seq_var.empty()) {
2763 VarOrRVar seq(seq_var, (rvars.find(seq_var) != rvars.end()));
2764 f_handle.reorder(seq, v);
2765 sched.push_schedule(f_handle.name(), g.output.stage_num,
2766 "reorder(" + seq_var + ", " + var + ")",
2767 {seq_var, var});
2768 }
2769 f_handle.parallel(v);
2770 sched.push_schedule(f_handle.name(), g.output.stage_num,
2771 "parallel(" + var + ")", {var});
2772 def_par = simplify(def_par * iter->second);
2773 } else {
2774 break;
2775 }
2776 }
2777 }
2778
2779 if (can_prove(def_par < arch_params.parallelism)) {
2780 user_warning << "Insufficient parallelism for " << f_handle.name() << "\n";
2781 }
2782
2783 // Find the level at which group members will be computed.
2784 int tile_inner_index = dims.size() - outer_dims.size() - 1;
2785 VarOrRVar tile_inner_var(Var::outermost());
2786 if (!outer_dims.empty()) {
2787 string var_name = get_base_name(dims[tile_inner_index].var);
2788 bool is_rvar = (rvars.find(var_name) != rvars.end());
2789 tile_inner_var = VarOrRVar(var_name, is_rvar);
2790 }
2791
2792 for (const FStage &mem : g.members) {
2793 // Skip member stages that have been inlined or stage that is the
2794 // output stage of the group
2795 if ((g.inlined.find(mem.func.name()) != g.inlined.end()) ||
2796 (mem.func.name() == g_out.name())) {
2797 continue;
2798 }
2799
2800 // Get the definition corresponding to the stage
2801 Definition mem_def = get_stage_definition(mem.func, mem.stage_num);
2802
2803 // Get the estimates for the dimensions of the member stage
2804 map<string, Expr> mem_estimates =
2805 bounds_to_estimates(get_element(group_loop_bounds, mem));
2806
2807 set<string> mem_rvars;
2808 vector<Dim> &mem_dims = mem_def.schedule().dims();
2809 for (int d = 0; d < (int)mem_dims.size() - 1; d++) {
2810 if (mem_dims[d].is_rvar()) {
2811 mem_rvars.insert(get_base_name(mem_dims[d].var));
2812 }
2813 }
2814
2815 // Get a function handle for scheduling the stage
2816 Stage mem_handle = Stage(Func(mem.func));
2817
2818 if (mem.stage_num > 0) {
2819 mem_handle = Func(mem.func).update(mem.stage_num - 1);
2820 } else {
2821 if (!outer_dims.empty()) {
2822 if (tile_inner_var.is_rvar) {
2823 Func(mem.func).compute_at(Func(g_out), tile_inner_var.rvar);
2824 } else {
2825 Func(mem.func).compute_at(Func(g_out), tile_inner_var.var);
2826 }
2827 string sanitized_g_out = get_sanitized_name(g_out.name());
2828 sched.push_schedule(mem_handle.name(), mem.stage_num,
2829 "compute_at(" + sanitized_g_out + ", " + tile_inner_var.name() + ")",
2830 {sanitized_g_out, tile_inner_var.name()});
2831 } else {
2832 user_warning << "Degenerate tiling. No dimensions are tiled"
2833 << "\n";
2834 user_warning << "Computing \"" << mem.func.name() << "\" at root"
2835 << "\n";
2836 Func(mem.func).compute_root();
2837 sched.push_schedule(mem_handle.name(), mem.stage_num, "compute_root()", {});
2838 }
2839 }
2840
2841 // Reorder the dimensions for better spatial locality. If we only have
2842 // one dimension (excluding __outermost), there is nothing to reorder.
2843 if (dims.size() > 2) {
2844 map<string, Expr> mem_strides =
2845 analyze_spatial_locality(mem, group_storage_bounds, inlines);
2846 if (!mem_strides.empty()) {
2847 reorder_dims(mem_handle, mem.stage_num, mem_def, mem_strides, sched);
2848 }
2849 }
2850
2851 vectorize_stage(g, mem_handle, mem.stage_num, mem_def, mem.func, false,
2852 t, mem_rvars, mem_estimates, sched);
2853 }
2854}
2855
2856void Partitioner::generate_cpu_schedule(const Target &t, AutoSchedule &sched) {
2857 // Grab the group bounds early as they rely on the dimensions of the group
2858 // outputs which will be altered by modifying schedules.
2859 map<FStage, map<FStage, DimBounds>> loop_bounds = group_loop_bounds();
2860 map<FStage, map<string, Box>> storage_bounds = group_storage_bounds();
2861
2862 set<string> inlines;
2863 // Mark all functions that are inlined.
2864 for (const pair<const FStage, Group> &g : groups) {
2865 for (const string &inline_func : g.second.inlined) {
2866 inlines.insert(inline_func);
2867 }
2868 }
2869
2870 // TODO: Inlining functions with update definitions has different
2871 // behavior than pure functions. They may need to be computed above
2872 // the innermost vector loop to avoid complications with varying
2873 // extents across different vector lanes.
2874 //
2875 // Since the default schedule is compute inline, we don't need to
2876 // explicitly call compute_inline() on the function.
2877
2878 // Realize schedule for each group in the pipeline.
2879 for (const auto &g : groups) {
2880 generate_group_cpu_schedule(g.second, t, get_element(loop_bounds, g.first),
2881 get_element(storage_bounds, g.first), inlines, sched);
2882 }
2883}
2884
2885Expr Partitioner::find_max_access_stride(const Scope<> &vars,
2886 const string &func_acc,
2887 const vector<Expr> &acc_exprs,
2888 const Box &buffer_bounds) {
2889 size_t num_storage_dims = 0;
2890 Expr bytes_per_ele = make_zero(Int(64));
2891
2892 // Get the number of dimensions of the allocated storage and the
2893 // number of bytes required to store a single value of func_acc.
2894 const auto &iter = dep_analysis.env.find(func_acc);
2895 if (iter != dep_analysis.env.end()) {
2896 const Function &f = iter->second;
2897 for (const auto &e : f.values()) {
2898 bytes_per_ele += e.type().bytes();
2899 }
2900 num_storage_dims = f.schedule().storage_dims().size();
2901 } else {
2902 bytes_per_ele = get_element(costs.inputs, func_acc).bytes();
2903 num_storage_dims = buffer_bounds.size();
2904 }
2905
2906 Expr curr_stride = bytes_per_ele;
2907 Expr stride = make_zero(Int(64));
2908
2909 internal_assert(num_storage_dims <= acc_exprs.size());
2910 for (size_t sdim = 0; sdim < num_storage_dims; sdim++) {
2911 // Check if the access expression depends on any of the loop variables
2912 // in 'vars'. Expressions that do not involve the variable have stride 0.
2913 if (expr_uses_vars(acc_exprs[sdim], vars)) {
2914 stride = max(stride, curr_stride);
2915 }
2916
2917 const Interval &dim_range = buffer_bounds[sdim];
2918 Expr dim_extent = get_extent(dim_range);
2919 if (!dim_extent.defined()) {
2920 return Expr();
2921 }
2922 curr_stride *= dim_extent;
2923 }
2924
2925 return simplify(stride);
2926}
2927
2928map<string, Expr>
2929Partitioner::analyze_spatial_locality(const FStage &stg,
2930 const map<string, Box> &allocation_bounds,
2931 const set<string> &inlines) {
2932 internal_assert(!stg.func.has_extern_definition());
2933 // Handle inlining. When a function is inlined into another, the stride of
2934 // the accesses should be computed on the expression post inlining.
2935 // For example:
2936 // f(x, y) = ...;
2937 // g(x, y) = f(y, x); // transpose
2938 // h(x, y) = g(y, x); // transpose
2939 //
2940 // If both g and f are inlined into h, then the resulting expression for h
2941 // will look like:
2942 // h(x, y) = f(x, y);
2943 //
2944 // Computing the stride of a loop over x in the function h will be incorrect
2945 // if inlining is not taken into account.
2946
2947 // Get all the allocations accessed in the definition corresponding to 'stg'.
2948 FindAllCalls find;
2949 Definition def = get_stage_definition(stg.func, stg.stage_num);
2950 // Perform inlining on the all the values and the args in the stage.
2951 for (auto &val : def.values()) {
2952 val = perform_inline(val, dep_analysis.env, inlines, dep_analysis.order);
2953 }
2954 for (auto &arg : def.args()) {
2955 arg = perform_inline(arg, dep_analysis.env, inlines, dep_analysis.order);
2956 }
2957 def.accept(&find);
2958
2959 // Arguments on the left hand side might themselves involve accesses
2960 // to allocations and thus need to be accounted for when computing the
2961 // strides along each dimension.
2962 vector<pair<string, vector<Expr>>> &call_args = find.call_args;
2963 // Account for the spatial locality of the store. Add the access on the
2964 // left hand side to call_args.
2965 call_args.emplace_back(stg.func.name(), def.args());
2966
2967 // Map for holding the strides across each dimension
2968 map<string, Expr> var_strides;
2969 const vector<Dim> &dims = def.schedule().dims();
2970
2971 for (int d = 0; d < (int)dims.size() - 1; d++) {
2972 // Get all the variables involving the dimension in the definition.
2973 FindVarsUsingVar dep_vars(dims[d].var);
2974 def.accept(&dep_vars);
2975
2976 // Accumulate the stride of each access to a loop dimension.
2977 Expr total_stride = 0;
2978 for (const pair<string, vector<Expr>> &call : call_args) {
2979 Box call_alloc_reg;
2980 const auto &iter = allocation_bounds.find(call.first);
2981 if (iter != allocation_bounds.end()) {
2982 call_alloc_reg = iter->second;
2983 } else {
2984 call_alloc_reg = get_element(pipeline_bounds, call.first);
2985 }
2986 Expr current_stride = find_max_access_stride(dep_vars.vars, call.first,
2987 call.second, call_alloc_reg);
2988 if (!current_stride.defined()) {
2989 return map<string, Expr>();
2990 }
2991 total_stride += current_stride;
2992 }
2993 var_strides.emplace(dims[d].var, simplify(total_stride));
2994 }
2995
2996 return var_strides;
2997}
2998
2999// Verify that function 'f' does not have partially specified schedules/bounds.
3000// The current auto scheduler cannots handle such cases.
3001void validate_no_partial_schedules(const Function &f, bool is_output) {
3002 if (f.has_extern_definition()) {
3003 return;
3004 }
3005
3006 // Verify no compute_root or bounds are specified
3007 user_assert(f.schedule().compute_level().is_inlined())
3008 << "AutoSchedule: cannot auto-schedule function \"" << f.name()
3009 << "\" since it is scheduled to be computed at root\n";
3010
3011 user_assert(is_output || f.schedule().bounds().empty())
3012 << "AutoSchedule: cannot auto-schedule function \"" << f.name()
3013 << "\" since it has partially specified bounds\n";
3014
3015 int num_stages = f.updates().size() + 1;
3016 for (int stage = 0; stage < num_stages; ++stage) {
3017 const Definition &def = get_stage_definition(f, stage);
3018 const StageSchedule &schedule = def.schedule();
3019
3020 // Verify no splits are specified
3021 user_assert(schedule.splits().empty())
3022 << "AutoSchedule: cannot auto-schedule function \"" << f.name()
3023 << "\" since it has partially specified schedules at stage " << stage << "\n";
3024
3025 // Verify that none of the dimensions are scheduled to be parallelized or
3026 // vectorized, or unrolled.
3027 for (const auto &d : schedule.dims()) {
3028 user_assert(d.for_type == ForType::Serial)
3029 << "AutoSchedule: cannot auto-schedule function \"" << f.name()
3030 << "\" since stage " << stage << " is not serial at dim " << d.var << "\n";
3031 }
3032
3033 if (stage == 0) {
3034 // Since we can only specialize on a Func, we only need to check for no
3035 // specializations for the initial stage.
3036 user_assert(def.specializations().empty())
3037 << "AutoSchedule: cannot auto-schedule function \"" << f.name()
3038 << "\" since it has specializations\n";
3039
3040 // Verify that there is no loop reordering on the initial definition
3041 // (i.e. the Vars in the dim list should be in the same order as
3042 // the args in the LHS of the definition).
3043 internal_assert(schedule.dims().size() - 1 == def.args().size());
3044 for (size_t i = 0; i < def.args().size(); ++i) {
3045 const Variable *arg = def.args()[i].as<Variable>();
3046 internal_assert(arg);
3047 user_assert(arg->name == schedule.dims()[i].var)
3048 << "AutoSchedule: cannot auto-schedule function \"" << f.name()
3049 << "\" since dim \"" << arg->name << "\" at stage " << stage
3050 << " has been reordered\n";
3051 }
3052 } else {
3053 // Verify that there is no loop reordering on the update definition
3054 // (i.e. the Vars in the dim list should be in the same order as
3055 // the args in the LHS of the definition, the RVars in the dim list
3056 // should be in the same order as the RVars in the rvar list, and
3057 // all RVars should come before all Vars).
3058
3059 const vector<Dim> &dims = schedule.dims();
3060 const vector<ReductionVariable> &rvars = schedule.rvars();
3061 const vector<Expr> &args = f.definition().args();
3062 internal_assert(dims.size() - 1 >= rvars.size());
3063
3064 for (size_t i = 0; i < rvars.size(); ++i) {
3065 const Dim &d = dims[i];
3066 user_assert(d.is_rvar() && (d.var == rvars[i].var))
3067 << "AutoSchedule: cannot auto-schedule function \"" << f.name()
3068 << "\" since dim \"" << i << "\" at stage " << stage
3069 << " has been reordered\n";
3070 }
3071
3072 internal_assert(dims.size() - rvars.size() - 1 <= args.size());
3073 int last_index = -1;
3074 for (int i = rvars.size(); i < (int)dims.size() - 1; ++i) {
3075 const Dim &d = dims[i];
3076 user_assert(!d.is_rvar())
3077 << "AutoSchedule: cannot auto-schedule function \"" << f.name()
3078 << "\" since dim \"" << i << "\" at stage " << stage
3079 << " has been reordered\n";
3080
3081 const auto &iter =
3082 std::find_if(args.begin(), args.end(),
3083 [&d](const Expr &arg) {
3084 const Variable *v = arg.as<Variable>();
3085 return (d.var == v->name);
3086 });
3087 internal_assert(iter != args.end());
3088 int current_index = iter - args.begin();
3089 user_assert(current_index > last_index)
3090 << "AutoSchedule: cannot auto-schedule function \"" << f.name()
3091 << "\" since dim \"" << i << "\" at stage " << stage
3092 << " has been reordered\n";
3093 last_index = current_index;
3094 }
3095 }
3096 }
3097}
3098
3099// Return true if 'f' is used by some extern Func.
3100bool used_by_extern_func(const map<string, Function> &env, const Function &f) {
3101 for (const auto &iter : env) {
3102 for (const ExternFuncArgument &arg : iter.second.extern_arguments()) {
3103 if (arg.is_func()) {
3104 if (Function(arg.func).name() == f.name()) {
3105 return true;
3106 }
3107 }
3108 }
3109 }
3110 return false;
3111}
3112
3113// If the bounds of a Func are undefined, then we should just inline the Func
3114// as long as it is legal to inline or used by some extern Func.
3115set<string> get_unbounded_functions(const map<string, Box> &pipeline_bounds,
3116 const map<string, Function> &env) {
3117 set<string> unbounded;
3118 for (const auto &iter : env) {
3119 if (!pipeline_bounds.count(iter.first)) {
3120 debug(5) << "...Skip checking function \"" << iter.first
3121 << "\" since it does not have pipeline bounds\n";
3122 continue;
3123 }
3124 const Function &f = iter.second;
3125 if (!f.can_be_inlined() || used_by_extern_func(env, f)) {
3126 continue;
3127 }
3128 const Box &bound = get_element(pipeline_bounds, iter.first);
3129 if (is_box_unbounded(bound)) {
3130 unbounded.insert(iter.first);
3131 }
3132 }
3133 return unbounded;
3134}
3135
3136bool inline_unbounded(const vector<Function> &outputs,
3137 const vector<string> &order,
3138 const map<string, Function> &env,
3139 const set<string> &unbounded) {
3140 bool inlined = false;
3141 // The very last few functions in 'order' are the last to be realized in the
3142 // pipeline (the final producers) so there is no point in checking it.
3143 for (int i = 0; i < (int)order.size() - (int)outputs.size(); ++i) {
3144 const Function &f1 = env.at(order[i]);
3145 if (!unbounded.count(f1.name())) {
3146 continue;
3147 }
3148 inlined = true;
3149 debug(4) << "Function \"" << order[i] << "\" is unbounded\n";
3150 for (int j = i + 1; j < (int)order.size(); ++j) {
3151 internal_assert(order[i] != order[j]);
3152 const Function &f2 = env.at(order[j]);
3153 debug(5) << "Inline unbounded function \"" << f1.name()
3154 << "\" inside \"" << f2.name() << "\"\n";
3155 inline_function(f2, f1);
3156 }
3157 }
3158 return inlined;
3159}

3161} // anonymous namespace

3163// Generate schedules for all functions in the pipeline required to compute the
3164// outputs. This applies the schedules and returns a string representation of
3165// the schedules. The target architecture is specified by 'target'.
3166string generate_schedules(const vector<Function> &outputs, const Target &target,
3167 const MachineParams &arch_params) {
3168 // Make an environment map which is used throughout the auto scheduling process.
3169 map<string, Function> env;
3170 for (const Function &f : outputs) {
3171 map<string, Function> more_funcs = find_transitive_calls(f);
3172 env.insert(more_funcs.begin(), more_funcs.end());
3173 }
3174
3175 // Finalize all the LoopLevels
3176 for (auto &iter : env) {
3177 iter.second.lock_loop_levels();
3178 }
3179
3180 // Compute the topological order, before any trivial inlining (i.e. before
3181 // we remove any functions from 'env'). We need the full topological
3182 // order to pass to get_func() when generating the string representation
3183 // of the schedule.
3184 debug(2) << "Computing topological order...\n";
3185 vector<string> top_order = topological_order(outputs, env);
3186
3187 // Validate that none of the functions in the pipeline have partial schedules.
3188 debug(2) << "Validating no partial schedules...\n";
3189 for (const auto &iter : env) {
3190 bool is_output = false;
3191 for (const auto &o : outputs) {
3192 is_output |= iter.second.same_as(o);
3193 }
3194 validate_no_partial_schedules(iter.second, is_output);
3195 }
3196
3197 // The auto scheduling algorithm requires estimates on the outputs of the
3198 // pipeline to get quantitative estimates of costs for computing functions
3199 // in the pipeline.
3200 debug(2) << "Checking estimates on outputs...\n";
3201 check_estimates_on_outputs(outputs);
3202
3203 // Run a pre-pass that inline all trivial Funcs (i.e. if the cost of
3204 // computing a Func is about the same as calling that Func, we should
3205 // just inline it).
3206 debug(2) << "Inlining all trivial functions...\n";
3207 if (inline_all_trivial_functions(outputs, top_order, env)) {
3208 // If any of the Funcs is inlined, we need to recompute 'env', since some
3209 // of the Funcs are no longer used and need to be removed from 'env'.
3210 //
3211 // Instead of recomputing 'env', we could also remove the inlined Func
3212 // within inline_all_trivial_functions(); however, it is a bit tricky
3213 // to do when dealing with inlined tuple. Consider the following case:
3214 // f(x, y) = x + y;
3215 // g(x, y) = {x, f(x, y)};
3216 // h(x, y) = g(x, y)[0];
3217 // When 'g' is inlined in 'h', no one uses 'f' anymore and it can
3218 // be removed from 'env'. However, to know this, we need to trace
3219 // all the function calls within the pipeline. Thus, we might as well
3220 // recompute the 'env' from scratch.
3221 env.clear();
3222 for (const Function &f : outputs) {
3223 map<string, Function> more_funcs = find_transitive_calls(f);
3224 env.insert(more_funcs.begin(), more_funcs.end());
3225 }
3226 }
3227
3228 // Compute the realization order of the functions within the pipeline.
3229 vector<string> order = realization_order(outputs, env).first;
3230
3231 // Run a pre-pass that inline all Funcs which values are accessed by
3232 // another single Func in element-wise manner. We need to do this
3233 // repeatedly since some inlining decisions may enable further inlining
3234 // that previously not possible. Consider the following case:
3235 // f1(x) = x;
3236 // f2(x) = f1(x) + 2;
3237 // f3(x) = f1(x) * 2;
3238 // f4(x) = f2(x) + f3(x);
3239 // f5(x) = f4(x) + 3;
3240 // In the first iteration, we cannot inline 'f1' since it is used by two
3241 // functions: 'f2' and 'f3'. If 'f2' and 'f4' get inlined and 'f3' is only
3242 // used by 'f4', then 'f1' can now also be inlined.
3243 debug(2) << "Inlining all element-wise functions...\n";
3244 while (inline_all_element_wise_functions(outputs, order, env)) {
3245 // We need to recompute 'env' for the same reason as with
3246 // inline_all_trivial_functions
3247 env.clear();
3248 for (const Function &f : outputs) {
3249 map<string, Function> more_funcs = find_transitive_calls(f);
3250 env.insert(more_funcs.begin(), more_funcs.end());
3251 }
3252 order = realization_order(outputs, env).first;
3253 }
3254
3255 // Compute the bounds of function values which are used for dependence analysis.
3256 debug(2) << "Computing function value bounds...\n";
3257 FuncValueBounds func_val_bounds = compute_function_value_bounds(order, env);
3258
3259 // Initialize the cost model.
3260 // Compute the expression costs for each function in the pipeline.
3261 debug(2) << "Initializing region costs...\n";
3262 RegionCosts costs(env, order);
3263 if (debug::debug_level() >= 3) {
3264 costs.disp_func_costs();
3265 }
3266
3267 debug(2) << "Initializing dependence analysis...\n";
3268 DependenceAnalysis dep_analysis(env, order, func_val_bounds);
3269
3270 // Compute bounds of all functions in the pipeline given estimates on
3271 // outputs. Also report functions which bounds could not be inferred.
3272 debug(2) << "Computing pipeline bounds...\n";
3273 map<string, Box> pipeline_bounds =
3274 get_pipeline_bounds(dep_analysis, outputs, &costs.input_estimates);
3275
3276 // Determine all unbounded functions that are not extern Func or
3277 // used by some extern Funcs.
3278 debug(2) << "Determining all unbounded functions...\n";
3279 set<string> unbounded = get_unbounded_functions(pipeline_bounds, env);
3280 if (!unbounded.empty()) {
3281 // If some functions are unbounded, we should inline those directly.
3282 // Also, we need to recompute 'env' and re-initialize 'costs' and
3283 // 'dep_analysis'
3284 debug(2) << "Inlining all unbounded functions...\n";
3285 internal_assert(inline_unbounded(outputs, order, env, unbounded));
3286
3287 env.clear();
3288 for (const Function &f : outputs) {
3289 map<string, Function> more_funcs = find_transitive_calls(f);
3290 env.insert(more_funcs.begin(), more_funcs.end());
3291 }
3292 order = realization_order(outputs, env).first;
3293
3294 debug(2) << "Re-computing function value bounds...\n";
3295 func_val_bounds = compute_function_value_bounds(order, env);
3296 debug(2) << "Re-initializing region costs...\n";
3297 RegionCosts costs(env, order);
3298 debug(2) << "Re-initializing dependence analysis...\n";
3299 dep_analysis = DependenceAnalysis(env, order, func_val_bounds);
3300 debug(2) << "Re-computing pipeline bounds...\n";
3301 pipeline_bounds = get_pipeline_bounds(dep_analysis, outputs, &costs.input_estimates);
3302 }
3303
3304 debug(2) << "Initializing partitioner...\n";
3305 Partitioner part(pipeline_bounds, arch_params, outputs, dep_analysis, costs);
3306
3307 // Compute and display reuse
3308 /* TODO: Use the reuse estimates to reorder loops
3309 for (const auto &f : env) {
3310 FindAllCalls find;
3311 f.second.accept(&find);
3312 int num_stages = f.second.updates().size() + 1;
3313 for (int s = 0; s < num_stages; s++) {
3314 FStage curr_s(f.second, s);
3315 map<string, Expr> reuse = part.evaluate_reuse(curr_s, find.funcs_called);
3316 debug(0) << curr_s << "\n";
3317 for (const auto &dir : reuse) {
3318 debug(0) << dir.first << " " << dir.second << ",";
3319 }
3320 debug(0) << "\n";
3321 }
3322 }*/
3323
3324 // Display the current pipeline graph.
3325 // TODO: Output the graph in dot format.
3326 if (debug::debug_level() >= 3) {
3327 part.disp_pipeline_graph();
3328 part.disp_pipeline_bounds();
3329 }
3330
3331 debug(2) << "Partitioner initializing groups...\n";
3332 part.initialize_groups();
3333 if (debug::debug_level() >= 3) {
3334 part.disp_pipeline_costs();
3335 }
3336
3337 debug(2) << "Partitioner computing inline group...\n";
3338 part.group(Partitioner::Level::Inline);
3339 if (debug::debug_level() >= 3) {
3340 part.disp_grouping();
3341 }
3342
3343 debug(2) << "Partitioner computing fast-mem group...\n";
3344 part.grouping_cache.clear();
3345 part.group(Partitioner::Level::FastMem);
3346 if (debug::debug_level() >= 3) {
3347 part.disp_pipeline_costs();
3348 part.disp_grouping();
3349 part.disp_pipeline_graph();
3350 }
3351
3352 debug(2) << "Initializing AutoSchedule...\n";
3353 AutoSchedule sched(env, top_order);
3354 debug(2) << "Generating CPU schedule...\n";
3355 part.generate_cpu_schedule(target, sched);
3356
3357 std::ostringstream oss;
3358 oss << sched;
3359 string sched_string = oss.str();
3360
3361 debug(3) << "\n\n*******************************\nSchedule:\n"
3362 << "*******************************\n"
3363 << sched_string << "\n\n";
3364
3365 // TODO: Unify both inlining and grouping for fast mem
3366 // TODO: GPU scheduling
3367 // TODO: Hierarchical tiling
3368
3369 return sched_string;
3370}

3372struct Mullapudi2016 {
3373 void operator()(const Pipeline &pipeline, const Target &target, const MachineParams &arch_params, AutoSchedulerResults *outputs) {
3374 AutoSchedulerResults results;
3375 results.target = target;
3376 results.machine_params_string = arch_params.to_string();
3377
3378 user_assert(target.arch == Target::X86 || target.arch == Target::ARM ||
3379 target.arch == Target::POWERPC || target.arch == Target::MIPS)
3380 << "The Mullapudi2016 autoscheduler is not supported for the target: " << target.to_string();
3381 results.scheduler_name = "Mullapudi2016";
3382 std::vector<Function> pipeline_outputs;
3383 for (const Func &f : pipeline.outputs()) {
3384 pipeline_outputs.push_back(f.function());
3385 }
3386 results.schedule_source = generate_schedules(pipeline_outputs, target, arch_params);
3387 // this autoscheduler has no featurization
3388
3389 *outputs = results;
3390 }
